7//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8//
9// This file defines the function verifier interface, that can be used for some
10// sanity checking of input to the system.
11//
12// Note that this does not provide full `Java style' security and verifications,
13// instead it just tries to ensure that code is well-formed.
14//
15// * Both of a binary operator's parameters are of the same type
16// * Verify that the indices of mem access instructions match other operands
17// * Verify that arithmetic and other things are only performed on first-class
18// types. Verify that shifts & logicals only happen on integrals f.e.
19// * All of the constants in a switch statement are of the correct type
20// * The code is in valid SSA form
21// * It should be illegal to put a label into any other type (like a structure)
22// or to return one. [except constant arrays!]
23// * Only phi nodes can be self referential: 'add i32 %0, %0 ; <int>:0' is bad
24// * PHI nodes must have an entry for each predecessor, with no extras.
25// * PHI nodes must be the first thing in a basic block, all grouped together
26// * PHI nodes must have at least one entry
27// * All basic blocks should only end with terminator insts, not contain them
28// * The entry node to a function must not have predecessors
29// * All Instructions must be embedded into a basic block
30// * Functions cannot take a void-typed parameter
31// * Verify that a function's argument list agrees with it's declared type.
32// * It is illegal to specify a name for a void value.
33// * It is illegal to have a internal global value with no initializer
34// * It is illegal to have a ret instruction that returns a value that does not
35// agree with the function return value type.
36// * Function call argument types match the function prototype
37// * A landing pad is defined by a landingpad instruction, and can be jumped to
38// only by the unwind edge of an invoke instruction.
39// * A landingpad instruction must be the first non-PHI instruction in the
40// block.
41// * Landingpad instructions must be in a function with a personality function.
42// * All other things that are tested by asserts spread about the code...
43//
44//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

119struct VerifierSupport {
120 raw_ostream *OS;
121 const Module &M;
122 ModuleSlotTracker MST;
123 const DataLayout &DL;
124 LLVMContext &Context;
125
126 /// Track the brokenness of the module while recursively visiting.
127 bool Broken = false;
128 /// Broken debug info can be "recovered" from by stripping the debug info.
129 bool BrokenDebugInfo = false;
130 /// Whether to treat broken debug info as an error.
131 bool TreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError = true;
132
133 explicit VerifierSupport(raw_ostream *OS, const Module &M)
134 : OS(OS), M(M), MST(&M), DL(M.getDataLayout()), Context(M.getContext()) {}
135
136private:
137 void Write(const Module *M) {
138 *OS << "; ModuleID = '" << M->getModuleIdentifier() << "'\n";
139 }
140
141 void Write(const Value *V) {
142 if (V)
143 Write(*V);
144 }
145
146 void Write(const Value &V) {
147 if (isa<Instruction>(V)) {
148 V.print(*OS, MST);
149 *OS << '\n';
150 } else {
151 V.printAsOperand(*OS, true, MST);
152 *OS << '\n';
153 }
154 }
155
156 void Write(const Metadata *MD) {
157 if (!MD)
158 return;
159 MD->print(*OS, MST, &M);
160 *OS << '\n';
161 }
162
163 template <class T> void Write(const MDTupleTypedArrayWrapper<T> &MD) {
164 Write(MD.get());
165 }
166
167 void Write(const NamedMDNode *NMD) {
168 if (!NMD)
169 return;
170 NMD->print(*OS, MST);
171 *OS << '\n';
172 }
173
174 void Write(Type *T) {
175 if (!T)
176 return;
177 *OS << ' ' << *T;
178 }
179
180 void Write(const Comdat *C) {
181 if (!C)
182 return;
183 *OS << *C;
184 }
185
186 void Write(const APInt *AI) {
187 if (!AI)
188 return;
189 *OS << *AI << '\n';
190 }
191
192 void Write(const unsigned i) { *OS << i << '\n'; }
193
194 template <typename T> void Write(ArrayRef<T> Vs) {
195 for (const T &V : Vs)
196 Write(V);
197 }
198
199 template <typename T1, typename... Ts>
200 void WriteTs(const T1 &V1, const Ts &... Vs) {
201 Write(V1);
202 WriteTs(Vs...);
203 }
204
205 template <typename... Ts> void WriteTs() {}
206
207public:
208 /// A check failed, so printout out the condition and the message.
209 ///
210 /// This provides a nice place to put a breakpoint if you want to see why
211 /// something is not correct.
212 void CheckFailed(const Twine &Message) {
213 if (OS)
214 *OS << Message << '\n';
215 Broken = true;
216 }
217
218 /// A check failed (with values to print).
219 ///
220 /// This calls the Message-only version so that the above is easier to set a
221 /// breakpoint on.
222 template <typename T1, typename... Ts>
223 void CheckFailed(const Twine &Message, const T1 &V1, const Ts &... Vs) {
224 CheckFailed(Message);
225 if (OS)
226 WriteTs(V1, Vs...);
227 }
228
229 /// A debug info check failed.
230 void DebugInfoCheckFailed(const Twine &Message) {
231 if (OS)
232 *OS << Message << '\n';
233 Broken |= TreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError;
234 BrokenDebugInfo = true;
235 }
236
237 /// A debug info check failed (with values to print).
238 template <typename T1, typename... Ts>
239 void DebugInfoCheckFailed(const Twine &Message, const T1 &V1,
240 const Ts &... Vs) {
241 DebugInfoCheckFailed(Message);
242 if (OS)
243 WriteTs(V1, Vs...);
244 }
245};

256 /// When verifying a basic block, keep track of all of the
257 /// instructions we have seen so far.
258 ///
259 /// This allows us to do efficient dominance checks for the case when an
260 /// instruction has an operand that is an instruction in the same block.

262

268
269 /// Track all DICompileUnits visited.

271

273 Type *LandingPadResultTy;
274
275 /// Whether we've seen a call to @llvm.localescape in this function
276 /// already.
277 bool SawFrameEscape;
278
279 /// Whether the current function has a DISubprogram attached to it.
280 bool HasDebugInfo = false;
281
282 /// Whether source was present on the first DIFile encountered in each CU.
283 DenseMap<const DICompileUnit *, bool> HasSourceDebugInfo;
284
285 /// Stores the count of how many objects were passed to llvm.localescape for a
286 /// given function and the largest index passed to llvm.localrecover.
287 DenseMap<Function *, std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>> FrameEscapeInfo;

292
293 /// Cache of constants visited in search of ConstantExprs.
294 SmallPtrSet<const Constant *, 32> ConstantExprVisited;
295
296 /// Cache of declarations of the llvm.experimental.deoptimize.<ty> intrinsic.

298
299 // Verify that this GlobalValue is only used in this module.
300 // This map is used to avoid visiting uses twice. We can arrive at a user
301 // twice, if they have multiple operands. In particular for very large
302 // constant expressions, we can arrive at a particular user many times.
303 SmallPtrSet<const Value *, 32> GlobalValueVisited;
304
305 // Keeps track of duplicate function argument debug info.
306 SmallVector<const DILocalVariable *, 16> DebugFnArgs;

312public:
313 explicit Verifier(raw_ostream *OS, bool ShouldTreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError,
314 const Module &M)
315 : VerifierSupport(OS, M), LandingPadResultTy(nullptr),
316 SawFrameEscape(false), TBAAVerifyHelper(this) {
317 TreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError = ShouldTreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError;
318 }
319
320 bool hasBrokenDebugInfo() const { return BrokenDebugInfo; }
321
322 bool verify(const Function &F) {
323 assert(F.getParent() == &M &&
324 "An instance of this class only works with a specific module!");
325
326 // First ensure the function is well-enough formed to compute dominance
327 // information, and directly compute a dominance tree. We don't rely on the
328 // pass manager to provide this as it isolates us from a potentially
329 // out-of-date dominator tree and makes it significantly more complex to run
330 // this code outside of a pass manager.
331 // FIXME: It's really gross that we have to cast away constness here.
332 if (!F.empty())
333 DT.recalculate(const_cast<Function &>(F));
334
335 for (const BasicBlock &BB : F) {
336 if (!BB.empty() && BB.back().isTerminator())
337 continue;
338
339 if (OS) {
340 *OS << "Basic Block in function '" << F.getName()
341 << "' does not have terminator!\n";
342 BB.printAsOperand(*OS, true, MST);
343 *OS << "\n";
344 }
345 return false;
346 }
347
348 Broken = false;
349 // FIXME: We strip const here because the inst visitor strips const.
350 visit(const_cast<Function &>(F));
351 verifySiblingFuncletUnwinds();
352 InstsInThisBlock.clear();
353 DebugFnArgs.clear();
354 LandingPadResultTy = nullptr;
355 SawFrameEscape = false;
356 SiblingFuncletInfo.clear();
357
358 return !Broken;
359 }
360
361 /// Verify the module that this instance of \c Verifier was initialized with.
362 bool verify() {
363 Broken = false;
364
365 // Collect all declarations of the llvm.experimental.deoptimize intrinsic.
366 for (const Function &F : M)
367 if (F.getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_deoptimize)
368 DeoptimizeDeclarations.push_back(&F);
369
370 // Now that we've visited every function, verify that we never asked to
371 // recover a frame index that wasn't escaped.
372 verifyFrameRecoverIndices();
373 for (const GlobalVariable &GV : M.globals())
374 visitGlobalVariable(GV);
375
376 for (const GlobalAlias &GA : M.aliases())
377 visitGlobalAlias(GA);
378
379 for (const NamedMDNode &NMD : M.named_metadata())
380 visitNamedMDNode(NMD);
381
382 for (const StringMapEntry<Comdat> &SMEC : M.getComdatSymbolTable())
383 visitComdat(SMEC.getValue());
384
385 visitModuleFlags(M);
386 visitModuleIdents(M);
387 visitModuleCommandLines(M);
388
389 verifyCompileUnits();
390
391 verifyDeoptimizeCallingConvs();
392 DISubprogramAttachments.clear();
393 return !Broken;
394 }

533/// We know that cond should be true, if not print an error message.
534#define Assert(C, ...) \
535 do { if (!(C)) { CheckFailed(__VA_ARGS__); return; } } while (false)
536
537/// We know that a debug info condition should be true, if not print
538/// an error message.
539#define AssertDI(C, ...) \
540 do { if (!(C)) { DebugInfoCheckFailed(__VA_ARGS__); return; } } while (false)
541
542void Verifier::visit(Instruction &I) {
543 for (unsigned i = 0, e = I.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i)
544 Assert(I.getOperand(i) != nullptr, "Operand is null", &I);
545 InstVisitor<Verifier>::visit(I);
546}
547
548// Helper to recursively iterate over indirect users. By
549// returning false, the callback can ask to stop recursing
550// further.
551static void forEachUser(const Value *User,
552 SmallPtrSet<const Value *, 32> &Visited,
553 llvm::function_ref<bool(const Value *)> Callback) {
554 if (!Visited.insert(User).second)
555 return;
556 for (const Value *TheNextUser : User->materialized_users())
557 if (Callback(TheNextUser))
558 forEachUser(TheNextUser, Visited, Callback);
559}

561void Verifier::visitVAArgInst(VAArgInst &VAA) {
562 Assert(VAA.getPointerOperand()->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
563 DL.getAllocaAddrSpace(),
564 "va_arg not in alloca AS?", &VAA);
565 visitInstruction(VAA);
566}
567
568void Verifier::visitGlobalValue(const GlobalValue &GV) {
569 Assert(!GV.isDeclaration() || GV.hasValidDeclarationLinkage(),
570 "Global is external, but doesn't have external or weak linkage!", &GV);
571
572 Assert(GV.getAlignment() <= Value::MaximumAlignment,
573 "huge alignment values are unsupported", &GV);
574 Assert(!GV.hasAppendingLinkage() || isa<GlobalVariable>(GV),
575 "Only global variables can have appending linkage!", &GV);
576
577 if (GV.hasAppendingLinkage()) {
578 const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(&GV);
579 Assert(GVar && GVar->getValueType()->isArrayTy(),
580 "Only global arrays can have appending linkage!", GVar);
581 }
582
583 if (GV.isDeclarationForLinker())
584 Assert(!GV.hasComdat(), "Declaration may not be in a Comdat!", &GV);
585
586 if (GV.hasDLLImportStorageClass()) {
587 Assert(!GV.isDSOLocal(),
588 "GlobalValue with DLLImport Storage is dso_local!", &GV);
589
590 Assert((GV.isDeclaration() && GV.hasExternalLinkage()) ||
591 GV.hasAvailableExternallyLinkage(),
592 "Global is marked as dllimport, but not external", &GV);
593 }
594
595 if (GV.hasLocalLinkage())
596 Assert(GV.isDSOLocal(),
597 "GlobalValue with private or internal linkage must be dso_local!",
598 &GV);
599
600 if (!GV.hasDefaultVisibility() && !GV.hasExternalWeakLinkage())
601 Assert(GV.isDSOLocal(),
602 "GlobalValue with non default visibility must be dso_local!", &GV);
603
604 forEachUser(&GV, GlobalValueVisited, [&](const Value *V) -> bool {
605 if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
606 if (!I->getParent() || !I->getParent()->getParent())
607 CheckFailed("Global is referenced by parentless instruction!", &GV, &M,
608 I);
609 else if (I->getParent()->getParent()->getParent() != &M)
610 CheckFailed("Global is referenced in a different module!", &GV, &M, I,
611 I->getParent()->getParent(),
612 I->getParent()->getParent()->getParent());
613 return false;
614 } else if (const Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(V)) {
615 if (F->getParent() != &M)
616 CheckFailed("Global is used by function in a different module", &GV, &M,
617 F, F->getParent());
618 return false;
619 }
620 return true;
621 });
622}
623
624void Verifier::visitGlobalVariable(const GlobalVariable &GV) {
625 if (GV.hasInitializer()) {
626 Assert(GV.getInitializer()->getType() == GV.getValueType(),
627 "Global variable initializer type does not match global "
628 "variable type!",
629 &GV);
630 // If the global has common linkage, it must have a zero initializer and
631 // cannot be constant.
632 if (GV.hasCommonLinkage()) {
633 Assert(GV.getInitializer()->isNullValue(),
634 "'common' global must have a zero initializer!", &GV);
635 Assert(!GV.isConstant(), "'common' global may not be marked constant!",
636 &GV);
637 Assert(!GV.hasComdat(), "'common' global may not be in a Comdat!", &GV);
638 }
639 }
640
641 if (GV.hasName() && (GV.getName() == "llvm.global_ctors" ||
642 GV.getName() == "llvm.global_dtors")) {
643 Assert(!GV.hasInitializer() || GV.hasAppendingLinkage(),
644 "invalid linkage for intrinsic global variable", &GV);
645 // Don't worry about emitting an error for it not being an array,
646 // visitGlobalValue will complain on appending non-array.
647 if (ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(GV.getValueType())) {
648 StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(ATy->getElementType());
649 // For initializers/destructors the code pointer is in the program address space
650 auto CtorPointerAS = DL.getProgramAddressSpace();
651 if (isCheriPointer(CtorPointerAS, &DL)) {
652 // However, for CHERI we must ensure that the ctors/init_array section
653 // is only filled with virtual addresses and not capabilities
654 // FIXME: we should emit ptrdiff objects instead
655 CtorPointerAS = 0;
656 }
657 PointerType *FuncPtrTy =
658 FunctionType::get(Type::getVoidTy(Context), false)->
659 getPointerTo(CtorPointerAS);
660 Assert(STy &&
661 (STy->getNumElements() == 2 || STy->getNumElements() == 3) &&
662 STy->getTypeAtIndex(0u)->isIntegerTy(32),
663 "wrong type for intrinsic global variable", &GV);
664 Assert(STy->getTypeAtIndex(1)->isPointerTy() &&
665 STy->getTypeAtIndex(1)->getPointerAddressSpace() == 0,
666 "llvm.global_ctors/llvm.global_dtors second parameter must be a "
667 "pointer in AS0",
668 &GV);
669 Assert(STy->getTypeAtIndex(1) == FuncPtrTy,
670 "wrong type for llvm.global_ctors/llvm.global_dtors parameter 2",
671 STy->getTypeAtIndex(1));
672 Assert(STy->getNumElements() == 3,
673 "the third field of the element type is mandatory, "
674 "specify i8* null to migrate from the obsoleted 2-field form");
675 Type *ETy = STy->getTypeAtIndex(2);
676 Assert(ETy->isPointerTy() &&
677 cast<PointerType>(ETy)->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(8),
678 "wrong type for intrinsic global variable", &GV);
679 }
680 }
681
682 if (GV.hasName() && (GV.getName() == "llvm.used" ||
683 GV.getName() == "llvm.compiler.used")) {
684 Assert(!GV.hasInitializer() || GV.hasAppendingLinkage(),
685 "invalid linkage for intrinsic global variable", &GV);
686 Type *GVType = GV.getValueType();
687 if (ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(GVType)) {
688 PointerType *PTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(ATy->getElementType());
689 Assert(PTy, "wrong type for intrinsic global variable", &GV);
690 if (GV.hasInitializer()) {
691 const Constant *Init = GV.getInitializer();
692 const ConstantArray *InitArray = dyn_cast<ConstantArray>(Init);
693 Assert(InitArray, "wrong initalizer for intrinsic global variable",
694 Init);
695 for (Value *Op : InitArray->operands()) {
696 Value *V = Op->stripPointerCastsNoFollowAliases();
697 Assert(isa<GlobalVariable>(V) || isa<Function>(V) ||
698 isa<GlobalAlias>(V),
699 "invalid llvm.used member", V);
700 Assert(V->hasName(), "members of llvm.used must be named", V);
701 }
702 }
703 }
704 }
705
706 // Visit any debug info attachments.
707 SmallVector<MDNode *, 1> MDs;
708 GV.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_dbg, MDs);
709 for (auto *MD : MDs) {
710 if (auto *GVE = dyn_cast<DIGlobalVariableExpression>(MD))
711 visitDIGlobalVariableExpression(*GVE);
712 else
713 AssertDI(false, "!dbg attachment of global variable must be a "
714 "DIGlobalVariableExpression");
715 }
716
717 if (!GV.hasInitializer()) {
718 visitGlobalValue(GV);
719 return;
720 }
721
722 // Walk any aggregate initializers looking for bitcasts between address spaces
723 visitConstantExprsRecursively(GV.getInitializer());
724
725 visitGlobalValue(GV);
726}
727
728void Verifier::visitAliaseeSubExpr(const GlobalAlias &GA, const Constant &C) {
729 SmallPtrSet<const GlobalAlias*, 4> Visited;
730 Visited.insert(&GA);
731 visitAliaseeSubExpr(Visited, GA, C);
732}
733
734void Verifier::visitAliaseeSubExpr(SmallPtrSetImpl<const GlobalAlias*> &Visited,
735 const GlobalAlias &GA, const Constant &C) {
736 if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(&C)) {
737 Assert(!GV->isDeclarationForLinker(), "Alias must point to a definition",
738 &GA);
739
740 if (const auto *GA2 = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(GV)) {
741 Assert(Visited.insert(GA2).second, "Aliases cannot form a cycle", &GA);
742
743 Assert(!GA2->isInterposable(), "Alias cannot point to an interposable alias",
744 &GA);
745 } else {
746 // Only continue verifying subexpressions of GlobalAliases.
747 // Do not recurse into global initializers.
748 return;
749 }
750 }
751
752 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(&C))
753 visitConstantExprsRecursively(CE);
754
755 for (const Use &U : C.operands()) {
756 Value *V = &*U;
757 if (const auto *GA2 = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(V))
758 visitAliaseeSubExpr(Visited, GA, *GA2->getAliasee());
759 else if (const auto *C2 = dyn_cast<Constant>(V))
760 visitAliaseeSubExpr(Visited, GA, *C2);
761 }
762}
763
764void Verifier::visitGlobalAlias(const GlobalAlias &GA) {
765 Assert(GlobalAlias::isValidLinkage(GA.getLinkage()),
766 "Alias should have private, internal, linkonce, weak, linkonce_odr, "
767 "weak_odr, or external linkage!",
768 &GA);
769 const Constant *Aliasee = GA.getAliasee();
770 Assert(Aliasee, "Aliasee cannot be NULL!", &GA);
771 Assert(GA.getType() == Aliasee->getType(),
772 "Alias and aliasee types should match!", &GA);
773
774 Assert(isa<GlobalValue>(Aliasee) || isa<ConstantExpr>(Aliasee),
775 "Aliasee should be either GlobalValue or ConstantExpr", &GA);
776
777 visitAliaseeSubExpr(GA, *Aliasee);
778
779 visitGlobalValue(GA);
780}

782void Verifier::visitNamedMDNode(const NamedMDNode &NMD) {
783 // There used to be various other llvm.dbg.* nodes, but we don't support
784 // upgrading them and we want to reserve the namespace for future uses.
785 if (NMD.getName().startswith("llvm.dbg."))
786 AssertDI(NMD.getName() == "llvm.dbg.cu",
787 "unrecognized named metadata node in the llvm.dbg namespace",
788 &NMD);
789 for (const MDNode *MD : NMD.operands()) {
790 if (NMD.getName() == "llvm.dbg.cu")
791 AssertDI(MD && isa<DICompileUnit>(MD), "invalid compile unit", &NMD, MD);
792
793 if (!MD)
794 continue;
795
796 visitMDNode(*MD);
797 }
798}
799
800void Verifier::visitMDNode(const MDNode &MD) {
801 // Only visit each node once. Metadata can be mutually recursive, so this
802 // avoids infinite recursion here, as well as being an optimization.
803 if (!MDNodes.insert(&MD).second)
804 return;
805
806 switch (MD.getMetadataID()) {
807 default:
808 llvm_unreachable("Invalid MDNode subclass");
809 case Metadata::MDTupleKind:
810 break;
811#define HANDLE_SPECIALIZED_MDNODE_LEAF(CLASS) \
812 case Metadata::CLASS##Kind: \
813 visit##CLASS(cast<CLASS>(MD)); \
814 break;
815#include "llvm/IR/Metadata.def"
816 }
817
818 for (const Metadata *Op : MD.operands()) {
819 if (!Op)
820 continue;
821 Assert(!isa<LocalAsMetadata>(Op), "Invalid operand for global metadata!",
822 &MD, Op);
823 if (auto *N = dyn_cast<MDNode>(Op)) {
824 visitMDNode(*N);
825 continue;
826 }
827 if (auto *V = dyn_cast<ValueAsMetadata>(Op)) {
828 visitValueAsMetadata(*V, nullptr);
829 continue;
830 }
831 }
832
833 // Check these last, so we diagnose problems in operands first.
834 Assert(!MD.isTemporary(), "Expected no forward declarations!", &MD);
835 Assert(MD.isResolved(), "All nodes should be resolved!", &MD);
836}
837
838void Verifier::visitValueAsMetadata(const ValueAsMetadata &MD, Function *F) {
839 Assert(MD.getValue(), "Expected valid value", &MD);
840 Assert(!MD.getValue()->getType()->isMetadataTy(),
841 "Unexpected metadata round-trip through values", &MD, MD.getValue());
842
843 auto *L = dyn_cast<LocalAsMetadata>(&MD);
844 if (!L)
845 return;
846
847 Assert(F, "function-local metadata used outside a function", L);
848
849 // If this was an instruction, bb, or argument, verify that it is in the
850 // function that we expect.
851 Function *ActualF = nullptr;
852 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(L->getValue())) {
853 Assert(I->getParent(), "function-local metadata not in basic block", L, I);
854 ActualF = I->getParent()->getParent();
855 } else if (BasicBlock *BB = dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(L->getValue()))
856 ActualF = BB->getParent();
857 else if (Argument *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(L->getValue()))
858 ActualF = A->getParent();
859 assert(ActualF && "Unimplemented function local metadata case!");
860
861 Assert(ActualF == F, "function-local metadata used in wrong function", L);
862}
863
864void Verifier::visitMetadataAsValue(const MetadataAsValue &MDV, Function *F) {
865 Metadata *MD = MDV.getMetadata();
866 if (auto *N = dyn_cast<MDNode>(MD)) {
867 visitMDNode(*N);
868 return;
869 }
870
871 // Only visit each node once. Metadata can be mutually recursive, so this
872 // avoids infinite recursion here, as well as being an optimization.
873 if (!MDNodes.insert(MD).second)
874 return;
875
876 if (auto *V = dyn_cast<ValueAsMetadata>(MD))
877 visitValueAsMetadata(*V, F);
878}

924void Verifier::visitDIDerivedType(const DIDerivedType &N) {
925 // Common scope checks.
926 visitDIScope(N);
927
928 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_typedef ||
929 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_pointer_type ||
930 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_ptr_to_member_type ||
931 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_reference_type ||
932 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type ||
933 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_const_type ||
934 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_volatile_type ||
935 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_restrict_type ||
936 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_atomic_type ||
937 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_member ||
938 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_inheritance ||
939 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_friend,
940 "invalid tag", &N);
941 if (N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_ptr_to_member_type) {
942 AssertDI(isType(N.getRawExtraData()), "invalid pointer to member type", &N,
943 N.getRawExtraData());
944 }
945
946 AssertDI(isScope(N.getRawScope()), "invalid scope", &N, N.getRawScope());
947 AssertDI(isType(N.getRawBaseType()), "invalid base type", &N,
948 N.getRawBaseType());
949
950 if (N.getDWARFAddressSpace()) {
951 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_pointer_type ||
952 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_reference_type ||
953 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type,
954 "DWARF address space only applies to pointer or reference types",
955 &N);
956 }
957}

959/// Detect mutually exclusive flags.
960static bool hasConflictingReferenceFlags(unsigned Flags) {
961 return ((Flags & DINode::FlagLValueReference) &&
962 (Flags & DINode::FlagRValueReference)) ||
963 ((Flags & DINode::FlagTypePassByValue) &&
964 (Flags & DINode::FlagTypePassByReference));
965}

976void Verifier::visitDICompositeType(const DICompositeType &N) {
977 // Common scope checks.
978 visitDIScope(N);
979
980 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_array_type ||
981 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type ||
982 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type ||
983 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type ||
984 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type ||
985 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_variant_part,
986 "invalid tag", &N);
987
988 AssertDI(isScope(N.getRawScope()), "invalid scope", &N, N.getRawScope());
989 AssertDI(isType(N.getRawBaseType()), "invalid base type", &N,
990 N.getRawBaseType());
991
992 AssertDI(!N.getRawElements() || isa<MDTuple>(N.getRawElements()),
993 "invalid composite elements", &N, N.getRawElements());
994 AssertDI(isType(N.getRawVTableHolder()), "invalid vtable holder", &N,
995 N.getRawVTableHolder());
996 AssertDI(!hasConflictingReferenceFlags(N.getFlags()),
997 "invalid reference flags", &N);
998
999 if (N.isVector()) {
1000 const DINodeArray Elements = N.getElements();
1001 AssertDI(Elements.size() == 1 &&
1002 Elements[0]->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_subrange_type,
1003 "invalid vector, expected one element of type subrange", &N);
1004 }
1005
1006 if (auto *Params = N.getRawTemplateParams())
1007 visitTemplateParams(N, *Params);
1008
1009 if (N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type ||
1010 N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type) {
1011 AssertDI(N.getFile() && !N.getFile()->getFilename().empty(),
1012 "class/union requires a filename", &N, N.getFile());
1013 }
1014
1015 if (auto *D = N.getRawDiscriminator()) {
1016 AssertDI(isa<DIDerivedType>(D) && N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_variant_part,
1017 "discriminator can only appear on variant part");
1018 }
1019}

1021void Verifier::visitDISubroutineType(const DISubroutineType &N) {
1022 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_subroutine_type, "invalid tag", &N);
1023 if (auto *Types = N.getRawTypeArray()) {
1024 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Types), "invalid composite elements", &N, Types);
1025 for (Metadata *Ty : N.getTypeArray()->operands()) {
1026 AssertDI(isType(Ty), "invalid subroutine type ref", &N, Types, Ty);
1027 }
1028 }
1029 AssertDI(!hasConflictingReferenceFlags(N.getFlags()),
1030 "invalid reference flags", &N);
1031}

1033void Verifier::visitDIFile(const DIFile &N) {
1034 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_file_type, "invalid tag", &N);
1035 Optional<DIFile::ChecksumInfo<StringRef>> Checksum = N.getChecksum();
1036 if (Checksum) {
1037 AssertDI(Checksum->Kind <= DIFile::ChecksumKind::CSK_Last,
1038 "invalid checksum kind", &N);
1039 size_t Size;
1040 switch (Checksum->Kind) {
1041 case DIFile::CSK_MD5:
1042 Size = 32;
1043 break;
1044 case DIFile::CSK_SHA1:
1045 Size = 40;
1046 break;
1047 }
1048 AssertDI(Checksum->Value.size() == Size, "invalid checksum length", &N);
1049 AssertDI(Checksum->Value.find_if_not(llvm::isHexDigit) == StringRef::npos,
1050 "invalid checksum", &N);
1051 }
1052}

1054void Verifier::visitDICompileUnit(const DICompileUnit &N) {
1055 AssertDI(N.isDistinct(), "compile units must be distinct", &N);
1056 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_compile_unit, "invalid tag", &N);
1057
1058 // Don't bother verifying the compilation directory or producer string
1059 // as those could be empty.
1060 AssertDI(N.getRawFile() && isa<DIFile>(N.getRawFile()), "invalid file", &N,
1061 N.getRawFile());
1062 AssertDI(!N.getFile()->getFilename().empty(), "invalid filename", &N,
1063 N.getFile());
1064
1065 verifySourceDebugInfo(N, *N.getFile());
1066
1067 AssertDI((N.getEmissionKind() <= DICompileUnit::LastEmissionKind),
1068 "invalid emission kind", &N);
1069
1070 if (auto *Array = N.getRawEnumTypes()) {
1071 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Array), "invalid enum list", &N, Array);
1072 for (Metadata *Op : N.getEnumTypes()->operands()) {
1073 auto *Enum = dyn_cast_or_null<DICompositeType>(Op);
1074 AssertDI(Enum && Enum->getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type,
1075 "invalid enum type", &N, N.getEnumTypes(), Op);
1076 }
1077 }
1078 if (auto *Array = N.getRawRetainedTypes()) {
1079 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Array), "invalid retained type list", &N, Array);
1080 for (Metadata *Op : N.getRetainedTypes()->operands()) {
1081 AssertDI(Op && (isa<DIType>(Op) ||
1082 (isa<DISubprogram>(Op) &&
1083 !cast<DISubprogram>(Op)->isDefinition())),
1084 "invalid retained type", &N, Op);
1085 }
1086 }
1087 if (auto *Array = N.getRawGlobalVariables()) {
1088 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Array), "invalid global variable list", &N, Array);
1089 for (Metadata *Op : N.getGlobalVariables()->operands()) {
1090 AssertDI(Op && (isa<DIGlobalVariableExpression>(Op)),
1091 "invalid global variable ref", &N, Op);
1092 }
1093 }
1094 if (auto *Array = N.getRawImportedEntities()) {
1095 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Array), "invalid imported entity list", &N, Array);
1096 for (Metadata *Op : N.getImportedEntities()->operands()) {
1097 AssertDI(Op && isa<DIImportedEntity>(Op), "invalid imported entity ref",
1098 &N, Op);
1099 }
1100 }
1101 if (auto *Array = N.getRawMacros()) {
1102 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Array), "invalid macro list", &N, Array);
1103 for (Metadata *Op : N.getMacros()->operands()) {
1104 AssertDI(Op && isa<DIMacroNode>(Op), "invalid macro ref", &N, Op);
1105 }
1106 }
1107 CUVisited.insert(&N);
1108}

1110void Verifier::visitDISubprogram(const DISubprogram &N) {
1111 AssertDI(N.getTag() == dwarf::DW_TAG_subprogram, "invalid tag", &N);
1112 AssertDI(isScope(N.getRawScope()), "invalid scope", &N, N.getRawScope());
1113 if (auto *F = N.getRawFile())
1114 AssertDI(isa<DIFile>(F), "invalid file", &N, F);
1115 else
1116 AssertDI(N.getLine() == 0, "line specified with no file", &N, N.getLine());
1117 if (auto *T = N.getRawType())
1118 AssertDI(isa<DISubroutineType>(T), "invalid subroutine type", &N, T);
1119 AssertDI(isType(N.getRawContainingType()), "invalid containing type", &N,
1120 N.getRawContainingType());
1121 if (auto *Params = N.getRawTemplateParams())
1122 visitTemplateParams(N, *Params);
1123 if (auto *S = N.getRawDeclaration())
1124 AssertDI(isa<DISubprogram>(S) && !cast<DISubprogram>(S)->isDefinition(),
1125 "invalid subprogram declaration", &N, S);
1126 if (auto *RawNode = N.getRawRetainedNodes()) {
1127 auto *Node = dyn_cast<MDTuple>(RawNode);
1128 AssertDI(Node, "invalid retained nodes list", &N, RawNode);
1129 for (Metadata *Op : Node->operands()) {
1130 AssertDI(Op && (isa<DILocalVariable>(Op) || isa<DILabel>(Op)),
1131 "invalid retained nodes, expected DILocalVariable or DILabel",
1132 &N, Node, Op);
1133 }
1134 }
1135 AssertDI(!hasConflictingReferenceFlags(N.getFlags()),
1136 "invalid reference flags", &N);
1137
1138 auto *Unit = N.getRawUnit();
1139 if (N.isDefinition()) {
1140 // Subprogram definitions (not part of the type hierarchy).
1141 AssertDI(N.isDistinct(), "subprogram definitions must be distinct", &N);
1142 AssertDI(Unit, "subprogram definitions must have a compile unit", &N);
1143 AssertDI(isa<DICompileUnit>(Unit), "invalid unit type", &N, Unit);
1144 if (N.getFile())
1145 verifySourceDebugInfo(*N.getUnit(), *N.getFile());
1146 } else {
1147 // Subprogram declarations (part of the type hierarchy).
1148 AssertDI(!Unit, "subprogram declarations must not have a compile unit", &N);
1149 }
1150
1151 if (auto *RawThrownTypes = N.getRawThrownTypes()) {
1152 auto *ThrownTypes = dyn_cast<MDTuple>(RawThrownTypes);
1153 AssertDI(ThrownTypes, "invalid thrown types list", &N, RawThrownTypes);
1154 for (Metadata *Op : ThrownTypes->operands())
1155 AssertDI(Op && isa<DIType>(Op), "invalid thrown type", &N, ThrownTypes,
1156 Op);
1157 }
1158
1159 if (N.areAllCallsDescribed())
1160 AssertDI(N.isDefinition(),
1161 "DIFlagAllCallsDescribed must be attached to a definition");
1162}

1207void Verifier::visitDIMacroFile(const DIMacroFile &N) {

1209 "invalid macinfo type", &N);
1210 if (auto *F = N.getRawFile())
1211 AssertDI(isa<DIFile>(F), "invalid file", &N, F);
1212
1213 if (auto *Array = N.getRawElements()) {
1214 AssertDI(isa<MDTuple>(Array), "invalid macro list", &N, Array);
1215 for (Metadata *Op : N.getElements()->operands()) {
1216 AssertDI(Op && isa<DIMacroNode>(Op), "invalid macro ref", &N, Op);
1217 }
1218 }
1219}

1332void Verifier::visitModuleIdents(const Module &M) {
1333 const NamedMDNode *Idents = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.ident");
1334 if (!Idents)
1335 return;
1336
1337 // llvm.ident takes a list of metadata entry. Each entry has only one string.
1338 // Scan each llvm.ident entry and make sure that this requirement is met.
1339 for (const MDNode *N : Idents->operands()) {
1340 Assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1,
1341 "incorrect number of operands in llvm.ident metadata", N);
1342 Assert(dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(N->getOperand(0)),
1343 ("invalid value for llvm.ident metadata entry operand"
1344 "(the operand should be a string)"),
1345 N->getOperand(0));
1346 }
1347}

1349void Verifier::visitModuleCommandLines(const Module &M) {
1350 const NamedMDNode *CommandLines = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.commandline");
1351 if (!CommandLines)
1352 return;
1353
1354 // llvm.commandline takes a list of metadata entry. Each entry has only one
1355 // string. Scan each llvm.commandline entry and make sure that this
1356 // requirement is met.
1357 for (const MDNode *N : CommandLines->operands()) {
1358 Assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1,
1359 "incorrect number of operands in llvm.commandline metadata", N);
1360 Assert(dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(N->getOperand(0)),
1361 ("invalid value for llvm.commandline metadata entry operand"
1362 "(the operand should be a string)"),
1363 N->getOperand(0));
1364 }
1365}
1366
1367void Verifier::visitModuleFlags(const Module &M) {
1368 const NamedMDNode *Flags = M.getModuleFlagsMetadata();
1369 if (!Flags) return;
1370
1371 // Scan each flag, and track the flags and requirements.
1372 DenseMap<const MDString*, const MDNode*> SeenIDs;
1373 SmallVector<const MDNode*, 16> Requirements;
1374 for (const MDNode *MDN : Flags->operands())
1375 visitModuleFlag(MDN, SeenIDs, Requirements);
1376
1377 // Validate that the requirements in the module are valid.
1378 for (const MDNode *Requirement : Requirements) {
1379 const MDString *Flag = cast<MDString>(Requirement->getOperand(0));
1380 const Metadata *ReqValue = Requirement->getOperand(1);
1381
1382 const MDNode *Op = SeenIDs.lookup(Flag);
1383 if (!Op) {
1384 CheckFailed("invalid requirement on flag, flag is not present in module",
1385 Flag);
1386 continue;
1387 }
1388
1389 if (Op->getOperand(2) != ReqValue) {
1390 CheckFailed(("invalid requirement on flag, "
1391 "flag does not have the required value"),
1392 Flag);
1393 continue;
1394 }
1395 }
1396}
1397
1398void
1399Verifier::visitModuleFlag(const MDNode *Op,
1400 DenseMap<const MDString *, const MDNode *> &SeenIDs,
1401 SmallVectorImpl<const MDNode *> &Requirements) {
1402 // Each module flag should have three arguments, the merge behavior (a
1403 // constant int), the flag ID (an MDString), and the value.
1404 Assert(Op->getNumOperands() == 3,
1405 "incorrect number of operands in module flag", Op);
1406 Module::ModFlagBehavior MFB;
1407 if (!Module::isValidModFlagBehavior(Op->getOperand(0), MFB)) {
1408 Assert(
1409 mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(Op->getOperand(0)),
1410 "invalid behavior operand in module flag (expected constant integer)",
1411 Op->getOperand(0));
1412 Assert(false,
1413 "invalid behavior operand in module flag (unexpected constant)",
1414 Op->getOperand(0));
1415 }
1416 MDString *ID = dyn_cast_or_null<MDString>(Op->getOperand(1));
1417 Assert(ID, "invalid ID operand in module flag (expected metadata string)",
1418 Op->getOperand(1));
1419
1420 // Sanity check the values for behaviors with additional requirements.
1421 switch (MFB) {
1422 case Module::Error:
1423 case Module::Warning:
1424 case Module::Override:
1425 // These behavior types accept any value.
1426 break;
1427
1428 case Module::Max: {
1429 Assert(mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(Op->getOperand(2)),
1430 "invalid value for 'max' module flag (expected constant integer)",
1431 Op->getOperand(2));
1432 break;
1433 }
1434
1435 case Module::Require: {
1436 // The value should itself be an MDNode with two operands, a flag ID (an
1437 // MDString), and a value.
1438 MDNode *Value = dyn_cast<MDNode>(Op->getOperand(2));
1439 Assert(Value && Value->getNumOperands() == 2,
1440 "invalid value for 'require' module flag (expected metadata pair)",
1441 Op->getOperand(2));
1442 Assert(isa<MDString>(Value->getOperand(0)),
1443 ("invalid value for 'require' module flag "
1444 "(first value operand should be a string)"),
1445 Value->getOperand(0));
1446
1447 // Append it to the list of requirements, to check once all module flags are
1448 // scanned.
1449 Requirements.push_back(Value);
1450 break;
1451 }
1452
1453 case Module::Append:
1454 case Module::AppendUnique: {
1455 // These behavior types require the operand be an MDNode.
1456 Assert(isa<MDNode>(Op->getOperand(2)),
1457 "invalid value for 'append'-type module flag "
1458 "(expected a metadata node)",
1459 Op->getOperand(2));
1460 break;
1461 }
1462 }
1463
1464 // Unless this is a "requires" flag, check the ID is unique.
1465 if (MFB != Module::Require) {
1466 bool Inserted = SeenIDs.insert(std::make_pair(ID, Op)).second;
1467 Assert(Inserted,
1468 "module flag identifiers must be unique (or of 'require' type)", ID);
1469 }
1470
1471 if (ID->getString() == "wchar_size") {
1472 ConstantInt *Value
1473 = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(Op->getOperand(2));
1474 Assert(Value, "wchar_size metadata requires constant integer argument");
1475 }
1476
1477 if (ID->getString() == "Linker Options") {
1478 // If the llvm.linker.options named metadata exists, we assume that the
1479 // bitcode reader has upgraded the module flag. Otherwise the flag might
1480 // have been created by a client directly.
1481 Assert(M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.linker.options"),
1482 "'Linker Options' named metadata no longer supported");
1483 }
1484
1485 if (ID->getString() == "CG Profile") {
1486 for (const MDOperand &MDO : cast<MDNode>(Op->getOperand(2))->operands())
1487 visitModuleFlagCGProfileEntry(MDO);
1488 }
1489}
1490
1491void Verifier::visitModuleFlagCGProfileEntry(const MDOperand &MDO) {
1492 auto CheckFunction = [&](const MDOperand &FuncMDO) {
1493 if (!FuncMDO)
1494 return;
1495 auto F = dyn_cast<ValueAsMetadata>(FuncMDO);
1496 Assert(F && isa<Function>(F->getValue()), "expected a Function or null",
1497 FuncMDO);
1498 };
1499 auto Node = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(MDO);
1500 Assert(Node && Node->getNumOperands() == 3, "expected a MDNode triple", MDO);
1501 CheckFunction(Node->getOperand(0));
1502 CheckFunction(Node->getOperand(1));
1503 auto Count = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantAsMetadata>(Node->getOperand(2));
1504 Assert(Count && Count->getType()->isIntegerTy(),
1505 "expected an integer constant", Node->getOperand(2));
1506}
1507
1508/// Return true if this attribute kind only applies to functions.
1509static bool isFuncOnlyAttr(Attribute::AttrKind Kind) {
1510 switch (Kind) {
1511 case Attribute::NoReturn:
1512 case Attribute::NoCfCheck:
1513 case Attribute::NoUnwind:
1514 case Attribute::NoInline:
1515 case Attribute::AlwaysInline:
1516 case Attribute::OptimizeForSize:
1517 case Attribute::StackProtect:
1518 case Attribute::StackProtectReq:
1519 case Attribute::StackProtectStrong:
1520 case Attribute::SafeStack:
1521 case Attribute::ShadowCallStack:
1522 case Attribute::NoRedZone:
1523 case Attribute::NoImplicitFloat:
1524 case Attribute::Naked:
1525 case Attribute::InlineHint:
1526 case Attribute::StackAlignment:
1527 case Attribute::UWTable:
1528 case Attribute::NonLazyBind:
1529 case Attribute::ReturnsTwice:
1530 case Attribute::SanitizeAddress:
1531 case Attribute::SanitizeHWAddress:
1532 case Attribute::SanitizeThread:
1533 case Attribute::SanitizeMemory:
1534 case Attribute::MinSize:
1535 case Attribute::NoDuplicate:
1536 case Attribute::Builtin:
1537 case Attribute::NoBuiltin:
1538 case Attribute::Cold:
1539 case Attribute::OptForFuzzing:
1540 case Attribute::OptimizeNone:
1541 case Attribute::JumpTable:
1542 case Attribute::Convergent:
1543 case Attribute::ArgMemOnly:
1544 case Attribute::NoRecurse:
1545 case Attribute::HasSideEffects:
1546 case Attribute::InaccessibleMemOnly:
1547 case Attribute::InaccessibleMemOrArgMemOnly:
1548 case Attribute::AllocSize:
1549 case Attribute::SpeculativeLoadHardening:
1550 case Attribute::Speculatable:
1551 case Attribute::StrictFP:
1552 return true;
1553 default:
1554 break;
1555 }
1556 return false;
1557}
1558
1559/// Return true if this is a function attribute that can also appear on
1560/// arguments.
1561static bool isFuncOrArgAttr(Attribute::AttrKind Kind) {
1562 return Kind == Attribute::ReadOnly || Kind == Attribute::WriteOnly ||
1563 Kind == Attribute::ReadNone;
1564}
1565
1566void Verifier::verifyAttributeTypes(AttributeSet Attrs, bool IsFunction,
1567 const Value *V) {
1568 for (Attribute A : Attrs) {
1569 if (A.isStringAttribute())
1570 continue;
1571
1572 if (isFuncOnlyAttr(A.getKindAsEnum())) {
1573 if (!IsFunction) {
1574 CheckFailed("Attribute '" + A.getAsString() +
1575 "' only applies to functions!",
1576 V);
1577 return;
1578 }
1579 } else if (IsFunction && !isFuncOrArgAttr(A.getKindAsEnum())) {
1580 CheckFailed("Attribute '" + A.getAsString() +
1581 "' does not apply to functions!",
1582 V);
1583 return;
1584 }
1585 }
1586}
1587
1588// VerifyParameterAttrs - Check the given attributes for an argument or return
1589// value of the specified type. The value V is printed in error messages.
1590void Verifier::verifyParameterAttrs(AttributeSet Attrs, Type *Ty,
1591 const Value *V) {
1592 if (!Attrs.hasAttributes())
1593 return;
1594
1595 verifyAttributeTypes(Attrs, /*IsFunction=*/false, V);
1596
1597 if (Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ImmArg)) {
1598 Assert(Attrs.getNumAttributes() == 1,
1599 "Attribute 'immarg' is incompatible with other attributes", V);
1600 }
1601
1602 // Check for mutually incompatible attributes. Only inreg is compatible with
1603 // sret.
1604 unsigned AttrCount = 0;
1605 AttrCount += Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ByVal);
1606 AttrCount += Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InAlloca);
1607 AttrCount += Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::StructRet) ||
1608 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InReg);
1609 AttrCount += Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Nest);
1610 Assert(AttrCount <= 1, "Attributes 'byval', 'inalloca', 'inreg', 'nest', "
1611 "and 'sret' are incompatible!",
1612 V);
1613
1614 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InAlloca) &&
1615 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadOnly)),
1616 "Attributes "
1617 "'inalloca and readonly' are incompatible!",
1618 V);
1619
1620 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::StructRet) &&
1621 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Returned)),
1622 "Attributes "
1623 "'sret and returned' are incompatible!",
1624 V);
1625
1626 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ZExt) &&
1627 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SExt)),
1628 "Attributes "
1629 "'zeroext and signext' are incompatible!",
1630 V);
1631
1632 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone) &&
1633 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadOnly)),
1634 "Attributes "
1635 "'readnone and readonly' are incompatible!",
1636 V);
1637
1638 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone) &&
1639 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::WriteOnly)),
1640 "Attributes "
1641 "'readnone and writeonly' are incompatible!",
1642 V);
1643
1644 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadOnly) &&
1645 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::WriteOnly)),
1646 "Attributes "
1647 "'readonly and writeonly' are incompatible!",
1648 V);
1649
1650 Assert(!(Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::NoInline) &&
1651 Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::AlwaysInline)),
1652 "Attributes "
1653 "'noinline and alwaysinline' are incompatible!",
1654 V);
1655
1656 if (Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ByVal) && Attrs.getByValType()) {
1657 Assert(Attrs.getByValType() == cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getElementType(),
1658 "Attribute 'byval' type does not match parameter!");
1659 }
1660
1661 AttrBuilder IncompatibleAttrs = AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(Ty);
1662 Assert(!AttrBuilder(Attrs).overlaps(IncompatibleAttrs),
1663 "Wrong types for attribute: " +
1664 AttributeSet::get(Context, IncompatibleAttrs).getAsString(),
1665 V);
1666
1667 if (PointerType *PTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty)) {
1668 SmallPtrSet<Type*, 4> Visited;
1669 if (!PTy->getElementType()->isSized(&Visited)) {
1670 Assert(!Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ByVal) &&
1671 !Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InAlloca),
1672 "Attributes 'byval' and 'inalloca' do not support unsized types!",
1673 V);
1674 }
1675 if (!isa<PointerType>(PTy->getElementType()))
1676 Assert(!Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SwiftError),
1677 "Attribute 'swifterror' only applies to parameters "
1678 "with pointer to pointer type!",
1679 V);
1680 } else {
1681 Assert(!Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ByVal),
1682 "Attribute 'byval' only applies to parameters with pointer type!",
1683 V);
1684 Assert(!Attrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SwiftError),
1685 "Attribute 'swifterror' only applies to parameters "
1686 "with pointer type!",
1687 V);
1688 }
1689}
1690
1691// Check parameter attributes against a function type.
1692// The value V is printed in error messages.
1693void Verifier::verifyFunctionAttrs(FunctionType *FT, AttributeList Attrs,
1694 const Value *V, bool IsIntrinsic) {
1695 if (Attrs.isEmpty())
1696 return;
1697
1698 bool SawNest = false;
1699 bool SawReturned = false;
1700 bool SawSRet = false;
1701 bool SawSwiftSelf = false;
1702 bool SawSwiftError = false;
1703
1704 // Verify return value attributes.
1705 AttributeSet RetAttrs = Attrs.getRetAttributes();
1706 Assert((!RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ByVal) &&
1707 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Nest) &&
1708 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::StructRet) &&
1709 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::NoCapture) &&
1710 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Returned) &&
1711 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InAlloca) &&
1712 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SwiftSelf) &&
1713 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SwiftError)),
1714 "Attributes 'byval', 'inalloca', 'nest', 'sret', 'nocapture', "
1715 "'returned', 'swiftself', and 'swifterror' do not apply to return "
1716 "values!",
1717 V);
1718 Assert((!RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadOnly) &&
1719 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::WriteOnly) &&
1720 !RetAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone)),
1721 "Attribute '" + RetAttrs.getAsString() +
1722 "' does not apply to function returns",
1723 V);
1724 verifyParameterAttrs(RetAttrs, FT->getReturnType(), V);
1725
1726 // Verify parameter attributes.
1727 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FT->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i) {
1728 Type *Ty = FT->getParamType(i);
1729 AttributeSet ArgAttrs = Attrs.getParamAttributes(i);
1730
1731 if (!IsIntrinsic) {
1732 Assert(!ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::ImmArg),
1733 "immarg attribute only applies to intrinsics",V);
1734 }
1735
1736 verifyParameterAttrs(ArgAttrs, Ty, V);
1737
1738 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Nest)) {
1739 Assert(!SawNest, "More than one parameter has attribute nest!", V);
1740 SawNest = true;
1741 }
1742
1743 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Returned)) {
1744 Assert(!SawReturned, "More than one parameter has attribute returned!",
1745 V);
1746 Assert(Ty->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(FT->getReturnType()),
1747 "Incompatible argument and return types for 'returned' attribute",
1748 V);
1749 SawReturned = true;
1750 }
1751
1752 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::StructRet)) {
1753 Assert(!SawSRet, "Cannot have multiple 'sret' parameters!", V);
1754 Assert(i == 0 || i == 1,
1755 "Attribute 'sret' is not on first or second parameter!", V);
1756 SawSRet = true;
1757 }
1758
1759 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SwiftSelf)) {
1760 Assert(!SawSwiftSelf, "Cannot have multiple 'swiftself' parameters!", V);
1761 SawSwiftSelf = true;
1762 }
1763
1764 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::SwiftError)) {
1765 Assert(!SawSwiftError, "Cannot have multiple 'swifterror' parameters!",
1766 V);
1767 SawSwiftError = true;
1768 }
1769
1770 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InAlloca)) {
1771 Assert(i == FT->getNumParams() - 1,
1772 "inalloca isn't on the last parameter!", V);
1773 }
1774 }
1775
1776 if (!Attrs.hasAttributes(AttributeList::FunctionIndex))
1777 return;
1778
1779 verifyAttributeTypes(Attrs.getFnAttributes(), /*IsFunction=*/true, V);
1780
1781 Assert(!(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone) &&
1782 Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReadOnly)),
1783 "Attributes 'readnone and readonly' are incompatible!", V);
1784
1785 Assert(!(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone) &&
1786 Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::WriteOnly)),
1787 "Attributes 'readnone and writeonly' are incompatible!", V);
1788
1789 Assert(!(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReadOnly) &&
1790 Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::WriteOnly)),
1791 "Attributes 'readonly and writeonly' are incompatible!", V);
1792
1793 Assert(!(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone) &&
1794 Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::InaccessibleMemOrArgMemOnly)),
1795 "Attributes 'readnone and inaccessiblemem_or_argmemonly' are "
1796 "incompatible!",
1797 V);
1798
1799 Assert(!(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::ReadNone) &&
1800 Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::InaccessibleMemOnly)),
1801 "Attributes 'readnone and inaccessiblememonly' are incompatible!", V);
1802
1803 Assert(!(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::NoInline) &&
1804 Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::AlwaysInline)),
1805 "Attributes 'noinline and alwaysinline' are incompatible!", V);
1806
1807 if (Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::OptimizeNone)) {
1808 Assert(Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::NoInline),
1809 "Attribute 'optnone' requires 'noinline'!", V);
1810
1811 Assert(!Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::OptimizeForSize),
1812 "Attributes 'optsize and optnone' are incompatible!", V);
1813
1814 Assert(!Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::MinSize),
1815 "Attributes 'minsize and optnone' are incompatible!", V);
1816 }
1817
1818 if (Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::JumpTable)) {
1819 const GlobalValue *GV = cast<GlobalValue>(V);
1820 Assert(GV->hasGlobalUnnamedAddr(),
1821 "Attribute 'jumptable' requires 'unnamed_addr'", V);
1822 }
1823
1824 if (Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::AllocSize)) {
1825 std::pair<unsigned, Optional<unsigned>> Args =
1826 Attrs.getAllocSizeArgs(AttributeList::FunctionIndex);
1827
1828 auto CheckParam = [&](StringRef Name, unsigned ParamNo) {
1829 if (ParamNo >= FT->getNumParams()) {
1830 CheckFailed("'allocsize' " + Name + " argument is out of bounds", V);
1831 return false;
1832 }
1833
1834 if (!FT->getParamType(ParamNo)->isIntegerTy()) {
1835 CheckFailed("'allocsize' " + Name +
1836 " argument must refer to an integer parameter",
1837 V);
1838 return false;
1839 }
1840
1841 return true;
1842 };
1843
1844 if (!CheckParam("element size", Args.first))
1845 return;
1846
1847 if (Args.second && !CheckParam("number of elements", *Args.second))
1848 return;
1849 }
1850}
1851
1852void Verifier::verifyFunctionMetadata(
1853 ArrayRef<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>> MDs) {
1854 for (const auto &Pair : MDs) {
1855 if (Pair.first == LLVMContext::MD_prof) {
1856 MDNode *MD = Pair.second;
1857 Assert(MD->getNumOperands() >= 2,
1858 "!prof annotations should have no less than 2 operands", MD);
1859
1860 // Check first operand.
1861 Assert(MD->getOperand(0) != nullptr, "first operand should not be null",
1862 MD);
1863 Assert(isa<MDString>(MD->getOperand(0)),
1864 "expected string with name of the !prof annotation", MD);
1865 MDString *MDS = cast<MDString>(MD->getOperand(0));
1866 StringRef ProfName = MDS->getString();
1867 Assert(ProfName.equals("function_entry_count") ||
1868 ProfName.equals("synthetic_function_entry_count"),
1869 "first operand should be 'function_entry_count'"
1870 " or 'synthetic_function_entry_count'",
1871 MD);
1872
1873 // Check second operand.
1874 Assert(MD->getOperand(1) != nullptr, "second operand should not be null",
1875 MD);
1876 Assert(isa<ConstantAsMetadata>(MD->getOperand(1)),
1877 "expected integer argument to function_entry_count", MD);
1878 }
1879 }
1880}
1881
1882void Verifier::visitConstantExprsRecursively(const Constant *EntryC) {
1883 if (!ConstantExprVisited.insert(EntryC).second)
1884 return;
1885
1886 SmallVector<const Constant *, 16> Stack;
1887 Stack.push_back(EntryC);
1888
1889 while (!Stack.empty()) {
1890 const Constant *C = Stack.pop_back_val();
1891
1892 // Check this constant expression.
1893 if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(C))
1894 visitConstantExpr(CE);
1895
1896 if (const auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(C)) {
1897 // Global Values get visited separately, but we do need to make sure
1898 // that the global value is in the correct module
1899 Assert(GV->getParent() == &M, "Referencing global in another module!",
1900 EntryC, &M, GV, GV->getParent());
1901 continue;
1902 }
1903
1904 // Visit all sub-expressions.
1905 for (const Use &U : C->operands()) {
1906 const auto *OpC = dyn_cast<Constant>(U);
1907 if (!OpC)
1908 continue;
1909 if (!ConstantExprVisited.insert(OpC).second)
1910 continue;
1911 Stack.push_back(OpC);
1912 }
1913 }
1914}
1915
1916void Verifier::visitConstantExpr(const ConstantExpr *CE) {
1917 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::BitCast)
1918 Assert(CastInst::castIsValid(Instruction::BitCast, CE->getOperand(0),
1919 CE->getType()),
1920 "Invalid bitcast", CE);
1921
1922 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::IntToPtr ||
1923 CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::PtrToInt) {
1924 auto *PtrTy = CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::IntToPtr
1925 ? CE->getType()
1926 : CE->getOperand(0)->getType();
1927 StringRef Msg = CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::IntToPtr
1928 ? "inttoptr not supported for non-integral pointers"
1929 : "ptrtoint not supported for non-integral pointers";
1930 Assert(
1931 !DL.isNonIntegralPointerType(cast<PointerType>(PtrTy->getScalarType())),
1932 Msg);
1933 }
1934}
1935
1936bool Verifier::verifyAttributeCount(AttributeList Attrs, unsigned Params) {
1937 // There shouldn't be more attribute sets than there are parameters plus the
1938 // function and return value.
1939 return Attrs.getNumAttrSets() <= Params + 2;
1940}

1942/// Verify that statepoint intrinsic is well formed.
1943void Verifier::verifyStatepoint(const CallBase &Call) {
1944 assert(Call.getCalledFunction() &&
1945 Call.getCalledFunction()->getIntrinsicID() ==
1946 Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint);
1947
1948 Assert(!Call.doesNotAccessMemory() && !Call.onlyReadsMemory() &&
1949 !Call.onlyAccessesArgMemory(),
1950 "gc.statepoint must read and write all memory to preserve "
1951 "reordering restrictions required by safepoint semantics",
1952 Call);
1953
1954 const int64_t NumPatchBytes =
1955 cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(1))->getSExtValue();
1956 assert(isInt<32>(NumPatchBytes) && "NumPatchBytesV is an i32!");
1957 Assert(NumPatchBytes >= 0,
1958 "gc.statepoint number of patchable bytes must be "
1959 "positive",
1960 Call);
1961
1962 const Value *Target = Call.getArgOperand(2);
1963 auto *PT = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Target->getType());
1964 Assert(PT && PT->getElementType()->isFunctionTy(),
1965 "gc.statepoint callee must be of function pointer type", Call, Target);
1966 FunctionType *TargetFuncType = cast<FunctionType>(PT->getElementType());
1967
1968 const int NumCallArgs = cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
1969 Assert(NumCallArgs >= 0,
1970 "gc.statepoint number of arguments to underlying call "
1971 "must be positive",
1972 Call);
1973 const int NumParams = (int)TargetFuncType->getNumParams();
1974 if (TargetFuncType->isVarArg()) {
1975 Assert(NumCallArgs >= NumParams,
1976 "gc.statepoint mismatch in number of vararg call args", Call);
1977
1978 // TODO: Remove this limitation
1979 Assert(TargetFuncType->getReturnType()->isVoidTy(),
1980 "gc.statepoint doesn't support wrapping non-void "
1981 "vararg functions yet",
1982 Call);
1983 } else
1984 Assert(NumCallArgs == NumParams,
1985 "gc.statepoint mismatch in number of call args", Call);
1986
1987 const uint64_t Flags
1988 = cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(4))->getZExtValue();
1989 Assert((Flags & ~(uint64_t)StatepointFlags::MaskAll) == 0,
1990 "unknown flag used in gc.statepoint flags argument", Call);
1991
1992 // Verify that the types of the call parameter arguments match
1993 // the type of the wrapped callee.
1994 AttributeList Attrs = Call.getAttributes();
1995 for (int i = 0; i < NumParams; i++) {
1996 Type *ParamType = TargetFuncType->getParamType(i);
1997 Type *ArgType = Call.getArgOperand(5 + i)->getType();
1998 Assert(ArgType == ParamType,
1999 "gc.statepoint call argument does not match wrapped "
2000 "function type",
2001 Call);
2002
2003 if (TargetFuncType->isVarArg()) {
2004 AttributeSet ArgAttrs = Attrs.getParamAttributes(5 + i);
2005 Assert(!ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::StructRet),
2006 "Attribute 'sret' cannot be used for vararg call arguments!",
2007 Call);
2008 }
2009 }
2010
2011 const int EndCallArgsInx = 4 + NumCallArgs;
2012
2013 const Value *NumTransitionArgsV = Call.getArgOperand(EndCallArgsInx + 1);
2014 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(NumTransitionArgsV),
2015 "gc.statepoint number of transition arguments "
2016 "must be constant integer",
2017 Call);
2018 const int NumTransitionArgs =
2019 cast<ConstantInt>(NumTransitionArgsV)->getZExtValue();
2020 Assert(NumTransitionArgs >= 0,
2021 "gc.statepoint number of transition arguments must be positive", Call);
2022 const int EndTransitionArgsInx = EndCallArgsInx + 1 + NumTransitionArgs;
2023
2024 const Value *NumDeoptArgsV = Call.getArgOperand(EndTransitionArgsInx + 1);
2025 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(NumDeoptArgsV),
2026 "gc.statepoint number of deoptimization arguments "
2027 "must be constant integer",
2028 Call);
2029 const int NumDeoptArgs = cast<ConstantInt>(NumDeoptArgsV)->getZExtValue();
2030 Assert(NumDeoptArgs >= 0,
2031 "gc.statepoint number of deoptimization arguments "
2032 "must be positive",
2033 Call);
2034
2035 const int ExpectedNumArgs =
2036 7 + NumCallArgs + NumTransitionArgs + NumDeoptArgs;
2037 Assert(ExpectedNumArgs <= (int)Call.arg_size(),
2038 "gc.statepoint too few arguments according to length fields", Call);
2039
2040 // Check that the only uses of this gc.statepoint are gc.result or
2041 // gc.relocate calls which are tied to this statepoint and thus part
2042 // of the same statepoint sequence
2043 for (const User *U : Call.users()) {
2044 const CallInst *UserCall = dyn_cast<const CallInst>(U);
2045 Assert(UserCall, "illegal use of statepoint token", Call, U);
2046 if (!UserCall)
2047 continue;
2048 Assert(isa<GCRelocateInst>(UserCall) || isa<GCResultInst>(UserCall),
2049 "gc.result or gc.relocate are the only value uses "
2050 "of a gc.statepoint",
2051 Call, U);
2052 if (isa<GCResultInst>(UserCall)) {
2053 Assert(UserCall->getArgOperand(0) == &Call,
2054 "gc.result connected to wrong gc.statepoint", Call, UserCall);
2055 } else if (isa<GCRelocateInst>(Call)) {
2056 Assert(UserCall->getArgOperand(0) == &Call,
2057 "gc.relocate connected to wrong gc.statepoint", Call, UserCall);
2058 }
2059 }
2060
2061 // Note: It is legal for a single derived pointer to be listed multiple
2062 // times. It's non-optimal, but it is legal. It can also happen after
2063 // insertion if we strip a bitcast away.
2064 // Note: It is really tempting to check that each base is relocated and
2065 // that a derived pointer is never reused as a base pointer. This turns
2066 // out to be problematic since optimizations run after safepoint insertion
2067 // can recognize equality properties that the insertion logic doesn't know
2068 // about. See example statepoint.ll in the verifier subdirectory
2069}
2070
2071void Verifier::verifyFrameRecoverIndices() {
2072 for (auto &Counts : FrameEscapeInfo) {
2073 Function *F = Counts.first;
2074 unsigned EscapedObjectCount = Counts.second.first;
2075 unsigned MaxRecoveredIndex = Counts.second.second;
2076 Assert(MaxRecoveredIndex <= EscapedObjectCount,
2077 "all indices passed to llvm.localrecover must be less than the "
2078 "number of arguments passed to llvm.localescape in the parent "
2079 "function",
2080 F);
2081 }

2083
2084static Instruction *getSuccPad(Instruction *Terminator) {
2085 BasicBlock *UnwindDest;
2086 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Terminator))
2087 UnwindDest = II->getUnwindDest();
2088 else if (auto *CSI = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(Terminator))
2089 UnwindDest = CSI->getUnwindDest();
2090 else
2091 UnwindDest = cast<CleanupReturnInst>(Terminator)->getUnwindDest();
2092 return UnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI();
2093}
2094
2095void Verifier::verifySiblingFuncletUnwinds() {
2096 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 8> Visited;
2097 SmallPtrSet<Instruction *, 8> Active;
2098 for (const auto &Pair : SiblingFuncletInfo) {
2099 Instruction *PredPad = Pair.first;
2100 if (Visited.count(PredPad))
2101 continue;
2102 Active.insert(PredPad);
2103 Instruction *Terminator = Pair.second;
2104 do {
2105 Instruction *SuccPad = getSuccPad(Terminator);
2106 if (Active.count(SuccPad)) {
2107 // Found a cycle; report error
2108 Instruction *CyclePad = SuccPad;
2109 SmallVector<Instruction *, 8> CycleNodes;
2110 do {
2111 CycleNodes.push_back(CyclePad);
2112 Instruction *CycleTerminator = SiblingFuncletInfo[CyclePad];
2113 if (CycleTerminator != CyclePad)
2114 CycleNodes.push_back(CycleTerminator);
2115 CyclePad = getSuccPad(CycleTerminator);
2116 } while (CyclePad != SuccPad);
2117 Assert(false, "EH pads can't handle each other's exceptions",
2118 ArrayRef<Instruction *>(CycleNodes));
2119 }
2120 // Don't re-walk a node we've already checked
2121 if (!Visited.insert(SuccPad).second)
2122 break;
2123 // Walk to this successor if it has a map entry.
2124 PredPad = SuccPad;
2125 auto TermI = SiblingFuncletInfo.find(PredPad);
2126 if (TermI == SiblingFuncletInfo.end())
2127 break;
2128 Terminator = TermI->second;
2129 Active.insert(PredPad);
2130 } while (true);
2131 // Each node only has one successor, so we've walked all the active
2132 // nodes' successors.
2133 Active.clear();
2134 }
2135}
2136
2137// visitFunction - Verify that a function is ok.
2138//
2139void Verifier::visitFunction(const Function &F) {
2140 visitGlobalValue(F);
2141
2142 // Check function arguments.
2143 FunctionType *FT = F.getFunctionType();
2144 unsigned NumArgs = F.arg_size();
2145
2146 Assert(&Context == &F.getContext(),
2147 "Function context does not match Module context!", &F);
2148
2149 Assert(!F.hasCommonLinkage(), "Functions may not have common linkage", &F);
2150 Assert(FT->getNumParams() == NumArgs,
2151 "# formal arguments must match # of arguments for function type!", &F,
2152 FT);
2153 Assert(F.getReturnType()->isFirstClassType() ||
2154 F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy() || F.getReturnType()->isStructTy(),
2155 "Functions cannot return aggregate values!", &F);
2156
2157 Assert(!F.hasStructRetAttr() || F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy(),
2158 "Invalid struct return type!", &F);
2159
2160 AttributeList Attrs = F.getAttributes();
2161
2162 Assert(verifyAttributeCount(Attrs, FT->getNumParams()),
2163 "Attribute after last parameter!", &F);
2164
2165 bool isLLVMdotName = F.getName().size() >= 5 &&
2166 F.getName().substr(0, 5) == "llvm.";
2167
2168 // Check function attributes.
2169 verifyFunctionAttrs(FT, Attrs, &F, isLLVMdotName);
2170
2171 // On function declarations/definitions, we do not support the builtin
2172 // attribute. We do not check this in VerifyFunctionAttrs since that is
2173 // checking for Attributes that can/can not ever be on functions.
2174 Assert(!Attrs.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::Builtin),
2175 "Attribute 'builtin' can only be applied to a callsite.", &F);
2176
2177 // Check that this function meets the restrictions on this calling convention.
2178 // Sometimes varargs is used for perfectly forwarding thunks, so some of these
2179 // restrictions can be lifted.
2180 switch (F.getCallingConv()) {
2181 default:
2182 case CallingConv::C:
2183 break;
2184 case CallingConv::AMDGPU_KERNEL:
2185 case CallingConv::SPIR_KERNEL:
2186 Assert(F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy(),
2187 "Calling convention requires void return type", &F);
2188 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2189 case CallingConv::AMDGPU_VS:
2190 case CallingConv::AMDGPU_HS:
2191 case CallingConv::AMDGPU_GS:
2192 case CallingConv::AMDGPU_PS:
2193 case CallingConv::AMDGPU_CS:
2194 Assert(!F.hasStructRetAttr(),
2195 "Calling convention does not allow sret", &F);
2196 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2197 case CallingConv::Fast:
2198 case CallingConv::Cold:
2199 case CallingConv::Intel_OCL_BI:
2200 case CallingConv::PTX_Kernel:
2201 case CallingConv::PTX_Device:
2202 Assert(!F.isVarArg(), "Calling convention does not support varargs or "
2203 "perfect forwarding!",
2204 &F);
2205 break;
2206 }
2207
2208 // Check that the argument values match the function type for this function...
2209 unsigned i = 0;
2210 for (const Argument &Arg : F.args()) {
2211 Assert(Arg.getType() == FT->getParamType(i),
2212 "Argument value does not match function argument type!", &Arg,
2213 FT->getParamType(i));
2214 Assert(Arg.getType()->isFirstClassType(),
2215 "Function arguments must have first-class types!", &Arg);
2216 if (!isLLVMdotName) {
2217 Assert(!Arg.getType()->isMetadataTy(),
2218 "Function takes metadata but isn't an intrinsic", &Arg, &F);
2219 Assert(!Arg.getType()->isTokenTy(),
2220 "Function takes token but isn't an intrinsic", &Arg, &F);
2221 }
2222
2223 // Check that swifterror argument is only used by loads and stores.
2224 if (Attrs.hasParamAttribute(i, Attribute::SwiftError)) {
2225 verifySwiftErrorValue(&Arg);
2226 }
2227 ++i;
2228 }
2229
2230 if (!isLLVMdotName)
2231 Assert(!F.getReturnType()->isTokenTy(),
2232 "Functions returns a token but isn't an intrinsic", &F);
2233
2234 // Get the function metadata attachments.
2235 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 4> MDs;
2236 F.getAllMetadata(MDs);
2237 assert(F.hasMetadata() != MDs.empty() && "Bit out-of-sync");
2238 verifyFunctionMetadata(MDs);
2239
2240 // Check validity of the personality function
2241 if (F.hasPersonalityFn()) {
2242 auto *Per = dyn_cast<Function>(F.getPersonalityFn()->stripPointerCasts());
2243 if (Per)
2244 Assert(Per->getParent() == F.getParent(),
2245 "Referencing personality function in another module!",
2246 &F, F.getParent(), Per, Per->getParent());
2247 }
2248
2249 if (F.isMaterializable()) {
2250 // Function has a body somewhere we can't see.
2251 Assert(MDs.empty(), "unmaterialized function cannot have metadata", &F,
2252 MDs.empty() ? nullptr : MDs.front().second);
2253 } else if (F.isDeclaration()) {
2254 for (const auto &I : MDs) {
2255 AssertDI(I.first != LLVMContext::MD_dbg,
2256 "function declaration may not have a !dbg attachment", &F);
2257 Assert(I.first != LLVMContext::MD_prof,
2258 "function declaration may not have a !prof attachment", &F);
2259
2260 // Verify the metadata itself.
2261 visitMDNode(*I.second);
2262 }
2263 Assert(!F.hasPersonalityFn(),
2264 "Function declaration shouldn't have a personality routine", &F);
2265 } else {
2266 // Verify that this function (which has a body) is not named "llvm.*". It
2267 // is not legal to define intrinsics.
2268 Assert(!isLLVMdotName, "llvm intrinsics cannot be defined!", &F);
2269
2270 // Check the entry node
2271 const BasicBlock *Entry = &F.getEntryBlock();
2272 Assert(pred_empty(Entry),
2273 "Entry block to function must not have predecessors!", Entry);
2274
2275 // The address of the entry block cannot be taken, unless it is dead.
2276 if (Entry->hasAddressTaken()) {
2277 Assert(!BlockAddress::lookup(Entry)->isConstantUsed(),
2278 "blockaddress may not be used with the entry block!", Entry);
2279 }
2280
2281 unsigned NumDebugAttachments = 0, NumProfAttachments = 0;
2282 // Visit metadata attachments.
2283 for (const auto &I : MDs) {
2284 // Verify that the attachment is legal.
2285 switch (I.first) {
2286 default:
2287 break;
2288 case LLVMContext::MD_dbg: {
2289 ++NumDebugAttachments;
2290 AssertDI(NumDebugAttachments == 1,
2291 "function must have a single !dbg attachment", &F, I.second);
2292 AssertDI(isa<DISubprogram>(I.second),
2293 "function !dbg attachment must be a subprogram", &F, I.second);
2294 auto *SP = cast<DISubprogram>(I.second);
2295 const Function *&AttachedTo = DISubprogramAttachments[SP];
2296 AssertDI(!AttachedTo || AttachedTo == &F,
2297 "DISubprogram attached to more than one function", SP, &F);
2298 AttachedTo = &F;
2299 break;
2300 }
2301 case LLVMContext::MD_prof:
2302 ++NumProfAttachments;
2303 Assert(NumProfAttachments == 1,
2304 "function must have a single !prof attachment", &F, I.second);
2305 break;
2306 }
2307
2308 // Verify the metadata itself.
2309 visitMDNode(*I.second);
2310 }
2311 }
2312
2313 // If this function is actually an intrinsic, verify that it is only used in
2314 // direct call/invokes, never having its "address taken".
2315 // Only do this if the module is materialized, otherwise we don't have all the
2316 // uses.
2317 if (F.getIntrinsicID() && F.getParent()->isMaterialized()) {
2318 const User *U;
2319 if (F.hasAddressTaken(&U))
2320 Assert(false, "Invalid user of intrinsic instruction!", U);
2321 }
2322
2323 auto *N = F.getSubprogram();
2324 HasDebugInfo = (N != nullptr);
2325 if (!HasDebugInfo)
2326 return;
2327
2328 // Check that all !dbg attachments lead to back to N (or, at least, another
2329 // subprogram that describes the same function).
2330 //
2331 // FIXME: Check this incrementally while visiting !dbg attachments.
2332 // FIXME: Only check when N is the canonical subprogram for F.
2333 SmallPtrSet<const MDNode *, 32> Seen;
2334 for (auto &BB : F)
2335 for (auto &I : BB) {
2336 // Be careful about using DILocation here since we might be dealing with
2337 // broken code (this is the Verifier after all).
2338 DILocation *DL =
2339 dyn_cast_or_null<DILocation>(I.getDebugLoc().getAsMDNode());
2340 if (!DL)
2341 continue;
2342 if (!Seen.insert(DL).second)
2343 continue;
2344
2345 Metadata *Parent = DL->getRawScope();
2346 AssertDI(Parent && isa<DILocalScope>(Parent),
2347 "DILocation's scope must be a DILocalScope", N, &F, &I, DL,
2348 Parent);
2349 DILocalScope *Scope = DL->getInlinedAtScope();
2350 if (Scope && !Seen.insert(Scope).second)
2351 continue;
2352
2353 DISubprogram *SP = Scope ? Scope->getSubprogram() : nullptr;
2354
2355 // Scope and SP could be the same MDNode and we don't want to skip
2356 // validation in that case
2357 if (SP && ((Scope != SP) && !Seen.insert(SP).second))
2358 continue;
2359
2360 // FIXME: Once N is canonical, check "SP == &N".
2361 AssertDI(SP->describes(&F),
2362 "!dbg attachment points at wrong subprogram for function", N, &F,
2363 &I, DL, Scope, SP);
2364 }
2365}
2366
2367// verifyBasicBlock - Verify that a basic block is well formed...
2368//
2369void Verifier::visitBasicBlock(BasicBlock &BB) {
2370 InstsInThisBlock.clear();
2371
2372 // Ensure that basic blocks have terminators!
2373 Assert(BB.getTerminator(), "Basic Block does not have terminator!", &BB);
2374
2375 // Check constraints that this basic block imposes on all of the PHI nodes in
2376 // it.
2377 if (isa<PHINode>(BB.front())) {
2378 SmallVector<BasicBlock*, 8> Preds(pred_begin(&BB), pred_end(&BB));
2379 SmallVector<std::pair<BasicBlock*, Value*>, 8> Values;
2380 llvm::sort(Preds);
2381 for (const PHINode &PN : BB.phis()) {
2382 // Ensure that PHI nodes have at least one entry!
2383 Assert(PN.getNumIncomingValues() != 0,
2384 "PHI nodes must have at least one entry. If the block is dead, "
2385 "the PHI should be removed!",
2386 &PN);
2387 Assert(PN.getNumIncomingValues() == Preds.size(),
2388 "PHINode should have one entry for each predecessor of its "
2389 "parent basic block!",
2390 &PN);
2391
2392 // Get and sort all incoming values in the PHI node...
2393 Values.clear();
2394 Values.reserve(PN.getNumIncomingValues());
2395 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PN.getNumIncomingValues(); i != e; ++i)
2396 Values.push_back(
2397 std::make_pair(PN.getIncomingBlock(i), PN.getIncomingValue(i)));
2398 llvm::sort(Values);
2399
2400 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Values.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2401 // Check to make sure that if there is more than one entry for a
2402 // particular basic block in this PHI node, that the incoming values are
2403 // all identical.
2404 //
2405 Assert(i == 0 || Values[i].first != Values[i - 1].first ||
2406 Values[i].second == Values[i - 1].second,
2407 "PHI node has multiple entries for the same basic block with "
2408 "different incoming values!",
2409 &PN, Values[i].first, Values[i].second, Values[i - 1].second);
2410
2411 // Check to make sure that the predecessors and PHI node entries are
2412 // matched up.
2413 Assert(Values[i].first == Preds[i],
2414 "PHI node entries do not match predecessors!", &PN,
2415 Values[i].first, Preds[i]);
2416 }
2417 }
2418 }
2419
2420 // Check that all instructions have their parent pointers set up correctly.
2421 for (auto &I : BB)
2422 {
2423 Assert(I.getParent() == &BB, "Instruction has bogus parent pointer!");
2424 }
2425}
2426
2427void Verifier::visitTerminator(Instruction &I) {
2428 // Ensure that terminators only exist at the end of the basic block.
2429 Assert(&I == I.getParent()->getTerminator(),
2430 "Terminator found in the middle of a basic block!", I.getParent());
2431 visitInstruction(I);
2432}
2433
2434void Verifier::visitBranchInst(BranchInst &BI) {
2435 if (BI.isConditional()) {
2436 Assert(BI.getCondition()->getType()->isIntegerTy(1),
2437 "Branch condition is not 'i1' type!", &BI, BI.getCondition());
2438 }
2439 visitTerminator(BI);
2440}

2442void Verifier::visitReturnInst(ReturnInst &RI) {
2443 Function *F = RI.getParent()->getParent();
2444 unsigned N = RI.getNumOperands();
2445 if (F->getReturnType()->isVoidTy())
2446 Assert(N == 0,
2447 "Found return instr that returns non-void in Function of void "
2448 "return type!",
2449 &RI, F->getReturnType());
2450 else
2451 Assert(N == 1 && F->getReturnType() == RI.getOperand(0)->getType(),
2452 "Function return type does not match operand "
2453 "type of return inst!",
2454 &RI, F->getReturnType());
2455
2456 // Check to make sure that the return value has necessary properties for
2457 // terminators...
2458 visitTerminator(RI);
2459}

2461void Verifier::visitSwitchInst(SwitchInst &SI) {
2462 // Check to make sure that all of the constants in the switch instruction
2463 // have the same type as the switched-on value.

2465 SmallPtrSet<ConstantInt*, 32> Constants;

2473 visitTerminator(SI);

2486void Verifier::visitCallBrInst(CallBrInst &CBI) {

2503 visitTerminator(CBI);
