2776/// visitPHINode - Ensure that a PHI node is well formed.
2777///
2778void Verifier::visitPHINode(PHINode &PN) {
2779 // Ensure that the PHI nodes are all grouped together at the top of the block.
2780 // This can be tested by checking whether the instruction before this is
2781 // either nonexistent (because this is begin()) or is a PHI node. If not,
2782 // then there is some other instruction before a PHI.
2783 Assert(&PN == &PN.getParent()->front() ||
2784 isa<PHINode>(--BasicBlock::iterator(&PN)),
2785 "PHI nodes not grouped at top of basic block!", &PN, PN.getParent());
2786
2787 // Check that a PHI doesn't yield a Token.
2788 Assert(!PN.getType()->isTokenTy(), "PHI nodes cannot have token type!");
2789
2790 // Check that all of the values of the PHI node have the same type as the
2791 // result, and that the incoming blocks are really basic blocks.
2792 for (Value *IncValue : PN.incoming_values()) {
2793 Assert(PN.getType() == IncValue->getType(),
2794 "PHI node operands are not the same type as the result!", &PN);
2795 }
2796
2797 // All other PHI node constraints are checked in the visitBasicBlock method.
2798
2799 visitInstruction(PN);
2800}
2801
2802void Verifier::visitCallBase(CallBase &Call) {
2803 Assert(Call.getCalledValue()->getType()->isPointerTy(),
2804 "Called function must be a pointer!", Call);
2805 PointerType *FPTy = cast<PointerType>(Call.getCalledValue()->getType());
2806
2807 Assert(FPTy->getElementType()->isFunctionTy(),
2808 "Called function is not pointer to function type!", Call);
2809
2810 Assert(FPTy->getElementType() == Call.getFunctionType(),
2811 "Called function is not the same type as the call!", Call);
2812
2813 FunctionType *FTy = Call.getFunctionType();
2814
2815 // Verify that the correct number of arguments are being passed
2816 if (FTy->isVarArg())
2817 Assert(Call.arg_size() >= FTy->getNumParams(),
2818 "Called function requires more parameters than were provided!",
2819 Call);
2820 else
2821 Assert(Call.arg_size() == FTy->getNumParams(),
2822 "Incorrect number of arguments passed to called function!", Call);
2823
2824 // Verify that all arguments to the call match the function type.
2825 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FTy->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i) {
2826 Assert(Call.getArgOperand(i)->getType() == FTy->getParamType(i),
2827 "Call parameter type does not match function signature!",
2828 Call.getArgOperand(i), FTy->getParamType(i), Call);
2829#if 0
2830 if (Call.paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::NonNull)) {
2831 Assert(!isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Call.getArgOperand(i)),
2832 "Call parameter " + Twine(i) +
2833 " is null constant but marked as nonnull",
2834 Call.getArgOperand(i), Call);
2835 }
2836#endif
2837 }
2838
2839 AttributeList Attrs = Call.getAttributes();
2840
2841 Assert(verifyAttributeCount(Attrs, Call.arg_size()),
2842 "Attribute after last parameter!", Call);
2843
2844 bool IsIntrinsic = Call.getCalledFunction() &&
2845 Call.getCalledFunction()->getName().startswith("llvm.");
2846
2847 Function *Callee
2848 = dyn_cast<Function>(Call.getCalledValue()->stripPointerCasts());
2849
2850 if (Attrs.hasAttribute(AttributeList::FunctionIndex, Attribute::Speculatable)) {
2851 // Don't allow speculatable on call sites, unless the underlying function
2852 // declaration is also speculatable.
2853 Assert(Callee && Callee->isSpeculatable(),
2854 "speculatable attribute may not apply to call sites", Call);
2855 }
2856
2857 // Verify call attributes.
2858 verifyFunctionAttrs(FTy, Attrs, &Call, IsIntrinsic);
2859
2860 // Conservatively check the inalloca argument.
2861 // We have a bug if we can find that there is an underlying alloca without
2862 // inalloca.
2863 if (Call.hasInAllocaArgument()) {
2864 Value *InAllocaArg = Call.getArgOperand(FTy->getNumParams() - 1);
2865 if (auto AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(InAllocaArg->stripInBoundsOffsets()))
2866 Assert(AI->isUsedWithInAlloca(),
2867 "inalloca argument for call has mismatched alloca", AI, Call);
2868 }
2869
2870 // For each argument of the callsite, if it has the swifterror argument,
2871 // make sure the underlying alloca/parameter it comes from has a swifterror as
2872 // well.
2873 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FTy->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i) {
2874 if (Call.paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::SwiftError)) {
2875 Value *SwiftErrorArg = Call.getArgOperand(i);
2876 if (auto AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(SwiftErrorArg->stripInBoundsOffsets())) {
2877 Assert(AI->isSwiftError(),
2878 "swifterror argument for call has mismatched alloca", AI, Call);
2879 continue;
2880 }
2881 auto ArgI = dyn_cast<Argument>(SwiftErrorArg);
2882 Assert(ArgI,
2883 "swifterror argument should come from an alloca or parameter",
2884 SwiftErrorArg, Call);
2885 Assert(ArgI->hasSwiftErrorAttr(),
2886 "swifterror argument for call has mismatched parameter", ArgI,
2887 Call);
2888 }
2889
2890 if (Attrs.hasParamAttribute(i, Attribute::ImmArg)) {
2891 // Don't allow immarg on call sites, unless the underlying declaration
2892 // also has the matching immarg.
2893 Assert(Callee && Callee->hasParamAttribute(i, Attribute::ImmArg),
2894 "immarg may not apply only to call sites",
2895 Call.getArgOperand(i), Call);
2896 }
2897
2898 if (Call.paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::ImmArg)) {
2899 Value *ArgVal = Call.getArgOperand(i);
2900 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(ArgVal) || isa<ConstantFP>(ArgVal),
2901 "immarg operand has non-immediate parameter", ArgVal, Call);
2902 }
2903 }
2904
2905 if (FTy->isVarArg()) {
2906 // FIXME? is 'nest' even legal here?
2907 bool SawNest = false;
2908 bool SawReturned = false;
2909
2910 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < FTy->getNumParams(); ++Idx) {
2911 if (Attrs.hasParamAttribute(Idx, Attribute::Nest))
2912 SawNest = true;
2913 if (Attrs.hasParamAttribute(Idx, Attribute::Returned))
2914 SawReturned = true;
2915 }
2916
2917 // Check attributes on the varargs part.
2918 for (unsigned Idx = FTy->getNumParams(); Idx < Call.arg_size(); ++Idx) {
2919 Type *Ty = Call.getArgOperand(Idx)->getType();
2920 AttributeSet ArgAttrs = Attrs.getParamAttributes(Idx);
2921 verifyParameterAttrs(ArgAttrs, Ty, &Call);
2922
2923 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Nest)) {
2924 Assert(!SawNest, "More than one parameter has attribute nest!", Call);
2925 SawNest = true;
2926 }
2927
2928 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::Returned)) {
2929 Assert(!SawReturned, "More than one parameter has attribute returned!",
2930 Call);
2931 Assert(Ty->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(FTy->getReturnType()),
2932 "Incompatible argument and return types for 'returned' "
2933 "attribute",
2934 Call);
2935 SawReturned = true;
2936 }
2937
2938 // Statepoint intrinsic is vararg but the wrapped function may be not.
2939 // Allow sret here and check the wrapped function in verifyStatepoint.
2940 if (!Call.getCalledFunction() ||
2941 Call.getCalledFunction()->getIntrinsicID() !=
2942 Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint)
2943 Assert(!ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::StructRet),
2944 "Attribute 'sret' cannot be used for vararg call arguments!",
2945 Call);
2946
2947 if (ArgAttrs.hasAttribute(Attribute::InAlloca))
2948 Assert(Idx == Call.arg_size() - 1,
2949 "inalloca isn't on the last argument!", Call);
2950 }
2951 }
2952
2953 // Verify that there's no metadata unless it's a direct call to an intrinsic.
2954 if (!IsIntrinsic) {
2955 for (Type *ParamTy : FTy->params()) {
2956 Assert(!ParamTy->isMetadataTy(),
2957 "Function has metadata parameter but isn't an intrinsic", Call);
2958 Assert(!ParamTy->isTokenTy(),
2959 "Function has token parameter but isn't an intrinsic", Call);
2960 }
2961 }
2962
2963 // Verify that indirect calls don't return tokens.
2964 if (!Call.getCalledFunction())
2965 Assert(!FTy->getReturnType()->isTokenTy(),
2966 "Return type cannot be token for indirect call!");
2967
2968 if (Function *F = Call.getCalledFunction())
2969 if (Intrinsic::ID ID = (Intrinsic::ID)F->getIntrinsicID())
2970 visitIntrinsicCall(ID, Call);
2971
2972 // Verify that a callsite has at most one "deopt", at most one "funclet" and
2973 // at most one "gc-transition" operand bundle.
2974 bool FoundDeoptBundle = false, FoundFuncletBundle = false,
2975 FoundGCTransitionBundle = false;
2976 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Call.getNumOperandBundles(); i < e; ++i) {
2977 OperandBundleUse BU = Call.getOperandBundleAt(i);
2978 uint32_t Tag = BU.getTagID();
2979 if (Tag == LLVMContext::OB_deopt) {
2980 Assert(!FoundDeoptBundle, "Multiple deopt operand bundles", Call);
2981 FoundDeoptBundle = true;
2982 } else if (Tag == LLVMContext::OB_gc_transition) {
2983 Assert(!FoundGCTransitionBundle, "Multiple gc-transition operand bundles",
2984 Call);
2985 FoundGCTransitionBundle = true;
2986 } else if (Tag == LLVMContext::OB_funclet) {
2987 Assert(!FoundFuncletBundle, "Multiple funclet operand bundles", Call);
2988 FoundFuncletBundle = true;
2989 Assert(BU.Inputs.size() == 1,
2990 "Expected exactly one funclet bundle operand", Call);
2991 Assert(isa<FuncletPadInst>(BU.Inputs.front()),
2992 "Funclet bundle operands should correspond to a FuncletPadInst",
2993 Call);
2994 }
2995 }
2996
2997 // Verify that each inlinable callsite of a debug-info-bearing function in a
2998 // debug-info-bearing function has a debug location attached to it. Failure to
2999 // do so causes assertion failures when the inliner sets up inline scope info.
3000 if (Call.getFunction()->getSubprogram() && Call.getCalledFunction() &&
3001 Call.getCalledFunction()->getSubprogram())
3002 AssertDI(Call.getDebugLoc(),
3003 "inlinable function call in a function with "
3004 "debug info must have a !dbg location",
3005 Call);
3006
3007 visitInstruction(Call);
3008}
3009
3010/// Two types are "congruent" if they are identical, or if they are both pointer
3011/// types with different pointee types and the same address space.
3012static bool isTypeCongruent(Type *L, Type *R) {
3013 if (L == R)
3014 return true;
3015 PointerType *PL = dyn_cast<PointerType>(L);
3016 PointerType *PR = dyn_cast<PointerType>(R);
3017 if (!PL || !PR)
3018 return false;
3019 return PL->getAddressSpace() == PR->getAddressSpace();
3020}
3021
3022static AttrBuilder getParameterABIAttributes(int I, AttributeList Attrs) {
3023 static const Attribute::AttrKind ABIAttrs[] = {
3024 Attribute::StructRet, Attribute::ByVal, Attribute::InAlloca,
3025 Attribute::InReg, Attribute::Returned, Attribute::SwiftSelf,
3026 Attribute::SwiftError};
3027 AttrBuilder Copy;
3028 for (auto AK : ABIAttrs) {
3029 if (Attrs.hasParamAttribute(I, AK))
3030 Copy.addAttribute(AK);
3031 }
3032 if (Attrs.hasParamAttribute(I, Attribute::Alignment))
3033 Copy.addAlignmentAttr(Attrs.getParamAlignment(I));
3034 return Copy;
3035}
3036
3037void Verifier::verifyMustTailCall(CallInst &CI) {
3038 Assert(!CI.isInlineAsm(), "cannot use musttail call with inline asm", &CI);
3039
3040 // - The caller and callee prototypes must match. Pointer types of
3041 // parameters or return types may differ in pointee type, but not
3042 // address space.
3043 Function *F = CI.getParent()->getParent();
3044 FunctionType *CallerTy = F->getFunctionType();
3045 FunctionType *CalleeTy = CI.getFunctionType();
3046 if (!CI.getCalledFunction() || !CI.getCalledFunction()->isIntrinsic()) {
3047 Assert(CallerTy->getNumParams() == CalleeTy->getNumParams(),
3048 "cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched parameter counts",
3049 &CI);
3050 for (int I = 0, E = CallerTy->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) {
3051 Assert(
3052 isTypeCongruent(CallerTy->getParamType(I), CalleeTy->getParamType(I)),
3053 "cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched parameter types", &CI);
3054 }
3055 }
3056 Assert(CallerTy->isVarArg() == CalleeTy->isVarArg(),
3057 "cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched varargs", &CI);
3058 Assert(isTypeCongruent(CallerTy->getReturnType(), CalleeTy->getReturnType()),
3059 "cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched return types", &CI);
3060
3061 // - The calling conventions of the caller and callee must match.
3062 Assert(F->getCallingConv() == CI.getCallingConv(),
3063 "cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched calling conv", &CI);
3064
3065 // - All ABI-impacting function attributes, such as sret, byval, inreg,
3066 // returned, and inalloca, must match.
3067 AttributeList CallerAttrs = F->getAttributes();
3068 AttributeList CalleeAttrs = CI.getAttributes();
3069 for (int I = 0, E = CallerTy->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) {
3070 AttrBuilder CallerABIAttrs = getParameterABIAttributes(I, CallerAttrs);
3071 AttrBuilder CalleeABIAttrs = getParameterABIAttributes(I, CalleeAttrs);
3072 Assert(CallerABIAttrs == CalleeABIAttrs,
3073 "cannot guarantee tail call due to mismatched ABI impacting "
3074 "function attributes",
3075 &CI, CI.getOperand(I));
3076 }
3077
3078 // - The call must immediately precede a :ref:`ret <i_ret>` instruction,
3079 // or a pointer bitcast followed by a ret instruction.
3080 // - The ret instruction must return the (possibly bitcasted) value
3081 // produced by the call or void.
3082 Value *RetVal = &CI;
3083 Instruction *Next = CI.getNextNode();
3084
3085 // Handle the optional bitcast.
3086 if (BitCastInst *BI = dyn_cast_or_null<BitCastInst>(Next)) {
3087 Assert(BI->getOperand(0) == RetVal,
3088 "bitcast following musttail call must use the call", BI);
3089 RetVal = BI;
3090 Next = BI->getNextNode();
3091 }
3092
3093 // Check the return.
3094 ReturnInst *Ret = dyn_cast_or_null<ReturnInst>(Next);
3095 Assert(Ret, "musttail call must precede a ret with an optional bitcast",
3096 &CI);
3097 Assert(!Ret->getReturnValue() || Ret->getReturnValue() == RetVal,
3098 "musttail call result must be returned", Ret);
3099}

3123void Verifier::visitUnaryOperator(UnaryOperator &U) {

3143/// visitBinaryOperator - Check that both arguments to the binary operator are
3144/// of the same type!
3145///
3146void Verifier::visitBinaryOperator(BinaryOperator &B) {
3147 Assert(B.getOperand(0)->getType() == B.getOperand(1)->getType(),
3148 "Both operands to a binary operator are not of the same type!", &B);
3149
3150 switch (B.getOpcode()) {
3151 // Check that integer arithmetic operators are only used with
3152 // integral operands.
3153 case Instruction::Add:
3154 case Instruction::Sub:
3155 case Instruction::Mul:
3156 case Instruction::SDiv:
3157 case Instruction::UDiv:
3158 case Instruction::SRem:
3159 case Instruction::URem:
3160 Assert(B.getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
3161 "Integer arithmetic operators only work with integral types!", &B);
3162 Assert(B.getType() == B.getOperand(0)->getType(),
3163 "Integer arithmetic operators must have same type "
3164 "for operands and result!",
3165 &B);
3166 break;
3167 // Check that floating-point arithmetic operators are only used with
3168 // floating-point operands.
3169 case Instruction::FAdd:
3170 case Instruction::FSub:
3171 case Instruction::FMul:
3172 case Instruction::FDiv:
3173 case Instruction::FRem:
3174 Assert(B.getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy(),
3175 "Floating-point arithmetic operators only work with "
3176 "floating-point types!",
3177 &B);
3178 Assert(B.getType() == B.getOperand(0)->getType(),
3179 "Floating-point arithmetic operators must have same type "
3180 "for operands and result!",
3181 &B);
3182 break;
3183 // Check that logical operators are only used with integral operands.
3184 case Instruction::And:
3185 case Instruction::Or:
3186 case Instruction::Xor:
3187 Assert(B.getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
3188 "Logical operators only work with integral types!", &B);
3189 Assert(B.getType() == B.getOperand(0)->getType(),
3190 "Logical operators must have same type for operands and result!",
3191 &B);
3192 break;
3193 case Instruction::Shl:
3194 case Instruction::LShr:
3195 case Instruction::AShr:
3196 Assert(B.getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
3197 "Shifts only work with integral types!", &B);
3198 Assert(B.getType() == B.getOperand(0)->getType(),
3199 "Shift return type must be same as operands!", &B);
3200 break;
3201 default:
3202 llvm_unreachable("Unknown BinaryOperator opcode!");
3203 }
3204
3205 visitInstruction(B);
3206}

3261void Verifier::visitGetElementPtrInst(GetElementPtrInst &GEP) {
3262 Type *TargetTy = GEP.getPointerOperandType()->getScalarType();
3263
3264 Assert(isa<PointerType>(TargetTy),
3265 "GEP base pointer is not a vector or a vector of pointers", &GEP);
3266 Assert(GEP.getSourceElementType()->isSized(), "GEP into unsized type!", &GEP);
3267
3268 SmallVector<Value*, 16> Idxs(GEP.idx_begin(), GEP.idx_end());
3269 Assert(all_of(
3270 Idxs, [](Value* V) { return V->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(); }),
3271 "GEP indexes must be integers", &GEP);
3272 Type *ElTy =
3273 GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(GEP.getSourceElementType(), Idxs);
3274 Assert(ElTy, "Invalid indices for GEP pointer type!", &GEP);
3275
3276 Assert(GEP.getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() &&
3277 GEP.getResultElementType() == ElTy,
3278 "GEP is not of right type for indices!", &GEP, ElTy);
3279
3280 if (GEP.getType()->isVectorTy()) {
3281 // Additional checks for vector GEPs.
3282 unsigned GEPWidth = GEP.getType()->getVectorNumElements();
3283 if (GEP.getPointerOperandType()->isVectorTy())
3284 Assert(GEPWidth == GEP.getPointerOperandType()->getVectorNumElements(),
3285 "Vector GEP result width doesn't match operand's", &GEP);
3286 for (Value *Idx : Idxs) {
3287 Type *IndexTy = Idx->getType();
3288 if (IndexTy->isVectorTy()) {
3289 unsigned IndexWidth = IndexTy->getVectorNumElements();
3290 Assert(IndexWidth == GEPWidth, "Invalid GEP index vector width", &GEP);
3291 }
3292 Assert(IndexTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
3293 "All GEP indices should be of integer type");
3294 }
3295 }
3296
3297 if (auto *PTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(GEP.getType())) {
3298 Assert(GEP.getAddressSpace() == PTy->getAddressSpace(),
3299 "GEP address space doesn't match type", &GEP);
3300 }
3301
3302 visitInstruction(GEP);
3303}

3305static bool isContiguous(const ConstantRange &A, const ConstantRange &B) {
3306 return A.getUpper() == B.getLower() || A.getLower() == B.getUpper();
3307}

3309void Verifier::visitRangeMetadata(Instruction &I, MDNode *Range, Type *Ty) {
3310 assert(Range && Range == I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range) &&
3311 "precondition violation");
3312
3313 unsigned NumOperands = Range->getNumOperands();
3314 Assert(NumOperands % 2 == 0, "Unfinished range!", Range);
3315 unsigned NumRanges = NumOperands / 2;
3316 Assert(NumRanges >= 1, "It should have at least one range!", Range);
3317
3318 ConstantRange LastRange(1, true); // Dummy initial value
3319 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumRanges; ++i) {
3320 ConstantInt *Low =
3321 mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(Range->getOperand(2 * i));
3322 Assert(Low, "The lower limit must be an integer!", Low);
3323 ConstantInt *High =
3324 mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(Range->getOperand(2 * i + 1));
3325 Assert(High, "The upper limit must be an integer!", High);
3326 Assert(High->getType() == Low->getType() && High->getType() == Ty,
3327 "Range types must match instruction type!", &I);
3328
3329 APInt HighV = High->getValue();
3330 APInt LowV = Low->getValue();
3331 ConstantRange CurRange(LowV, HighV);
3332 Assert(!CurRange.isEmptySet() && !CurRange.isFullSet(),
3333 "Range must not be empty!", Range);
3334 if (i != 0) {
3335 Assert(CurRange.intersectWith(LastRange).isEmptySet(),
3336 "Intervals are overlapping", Range);
3337 Assert(LowV.sgt(LastRange.getLower()), "Intervals are not in order",
3338 Range);
3339 Assert(!isContiguous(CurRange, LastRange), "Intervals are contiguous",
3340 Range);
3341 }
3342 LastRange = ConstantRange(LowV, HighV);
3343 }
3344 if (NumRanges > 2) {
3345 APInt FirstLow =
3346 mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(Range->getOperand(0))->getValue();
3347 APInt FirstHigh =
3348 mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(Range->getOperand(1))->getValue();
3349 ConstantRange FirstRange(FirstLow, FirstHigh);
3350 Assert(FirstRange.intersectWith(LastRange).isEmptySet(),
3351 "Intervals are overlapping", Range);
3352 Assert(!isContiguous(FirstRange, LastRange), "Intervals are contiguous",
3353 Range);
3354 }
3355}

3357void Verifier::checkAtomicMemAccessSize(Type *Ty, const Instruction *I) {
3358 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(Ty);
3359 Assert(Size >= 8, "atomic memory access' size must be byte-sized", Ty, I);
3360 Assert(!(Size & (Size - 1)),
3361 "atomic memory access' operand must have a power-of-two size", Ty, I);

3364void Verifier::visitLoadInst(LoadInst &LI) {
3365 PointerType *PTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(LI.getOperand(0)->getType());
3366 Assert(PTy, "Load operand must be a pointer.", &LI);
3367 Type *ElTy = LI.getType();
3368 Assert(LI.getAlignment() <= Value::MaximumAlignment,
3369 "huge alignment values are unsupported", &LI);
3370 Assert(ElTy->isSized(), "loading unsized types is not allowed", &LI);
3371 if (LI.isAtomic()) {
3372 Assert(LI.getOrdering() != AtomicOrdering::Release &&
3373 LI.getOrdering() != AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease,
3374 "Load cannot have Release ordering", &LI);
3375 Assert(LI.getAlignment() != 0,
3376 "Atomic load must specify explicit alignment", &LI);
3377 Assert(ElTy->isIntOrPtrTy() || ElTy->isFloatingPointTy(),
3378 "atomic load operand must have integer, pointer, or floating point "
3379 "type!",
3380 ElTy, &LI);
3381 checkAtomicMemAccessSize(ElTy, &LI);
3382 } else {
3383 Assert(LI.getSyncScopeID() == SyncScope::System,
3384 "Non-atomic load cannot have SynchronizationScope specified", &LI);
3385 }
3386
3387 visitInstruction(LI);
3388}

3436 isa<InvokeInst>(U),

3574
3575void Verifier::visitEHPadPredecessors(Instruction &I) {
3576 assert(I.isEHPad());
3577
3578 BasicBlock *BB = I.getParent();
3579 Function *F = BB->getParent();
3580
3581 Assert(BB != &F->getEntryBlock(), "EH pad cannot be in entry block.", &I);
3582
3583 if (auto *LPI = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(&I)) {
3584 // The landingpad instruction defines its parent as a landing pad block. The
3585 // landing pad block may be branched to only by the unwind edge of an
3586 // invoke.
3587 for (BasicBlock *PredBB : predecessors(BB)) {
3588 const auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(PredBB->getTerminator());
3589 Assert(II && II->getUnwindDest() == BB && II->getNormalDest() != BB,
3590 "Block containing LandingPadInst must be jumped to "
3591 "only by the unwind edge of an invoke.",
3592 LPI);
3593 }
3594 return;
3595 }
3596 if (auto *CPI = dyn_cast<CatchPadInst>(&I)) {
3597 if (!pred_empty(BB))
3598 Assert(BB->getUniquePredecessor() == CPI->getCatchSwitch()->getParent(),
3599 "Block containg CatchPadInst must be jumped to "
3600 "only by its catchswitch.",
3601 CPI);
3602 Assert(BB != CPI->getCatchSwitch()->getUnwindDest(),
3603 "Catchswitch cannot unwind to one of its catchpads",
3604 CPI->getCatchSwitch(), CPI);
3605 return;
3606 }
3607
3608 // Verify that each pred has a legal terminator with a legal to/from EH
3609 // pad relationship.
3610 Instruction *ToPad = &I;
3611 Value *ToPadParent = getParentPad(ToPad);
3612 for (BasicBlock *PredBB : predecessors(BB)) {
3613 Instruction *TI = PredBB->getTerminator();
3614 Value *FromPad;
3615 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(TI)) {
3616 Assert(II->getUnwindDest() == BB && II->getNormalDest() != BB,
3617 "EH pad must be jumped to via an unwind edge", ToPad, II);
3618 if (auto Bundle = II->getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_funclet))
3619 FromPad = Bundle->Inputs[0];
3620 else
3621 FromPad = ConstantTokenNone::get(II->getContext());
3622 } else if (auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(TI)) {
3623 FromPad = CRI->getOperand(0);
3624 Assert(FromPad != ToPadParent, "A cleanupret must exit its cleanup", CRI);
3625 } else if (auto *CSI = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(TI)) {
3626 FromPad = CSI;
3627 } else {
3628 Assert(false, "EH pad must be jumped to via an unwind edge", ToPad, TI);
3629 }
3630
3631 // The edge may exit from zero or more nested pads.
3632 SmallSet<Value *, 8> Seen;
3633 for (;; FromPad = getParentPad(FromPad)) {
3634 Assert(FromPad != ToPad,
3635 "EH pad cannot handle exceptions raised within it", FromPad, TI);
3636 if (FromPad == ToPadParent) {
3637 // This is a legal unwind edge.
3638 break;
3639 }
3640 Assert(!isa<ConstantTokenNone>(FromPad),
3641 "A single unwind edge may only enter one EH pad", TI);
3642 Assert(Seen.insert(FromPad).second,
3643 "EH pad jumps through a cycle of pads", FromPad);
3644 }
3645 }
3646}
3647
3648void Verifier::visitLandingPadInst(LandingPadInst &LPI) {
3649 // The landingpad instruction is ill-formed if it doesn't have any clauses and
3650 // isn't a cleanup.
3651 Assert(LPI.getNumClauses() > 0 || LPI.isCleanup(),
3652 "LandingPadInst needs at least one clause or to be a cleanup.", &LPI);
3653
3654 visitEHPadPredecessors(LPI);
3655
3656 if (!LandingPadResultTy)
3657 LandingPadResultTy = LPI.getType();
3658 else
3659 Assert(LandingPadResultTy == LPI.getType(),
3660 "The landingpad instruction should have a consistent result type "
3661 "inside a function.",
3662 &LPI);
3663
3664 Function *F = LPI.getParent()->getParent();
3665 Assert(F->hasPersonalityFn(),
3666 "LandingPadInst needs to be in a function with a personality.", &LPI);
3667
3668 // The landingpad instruction must be the first non-PHI instruction in the
3669 // block.
3670 Assert(LPI.getParent()->getLandingPadInst() == &LPI,
3671 "LandingPadInst not the first non-PHI instruction in the block.",
3672 &LPI);
3673
3674 for (unsigned i = 0, e = LPI.getNumClauses(); i < e; ++i) {
3675 Constant *Clause = LPI.getClause(i);
3676 if (LPI.isCatch(i)) {
3677 Assert(isa<PointerType>(Clause->getType()),
3678 "Catch operand does not have pointer type!", &LPI);
3679 } else {
3680 Assert(LPI.isFilter(i), "Clause is neither catch nor filter!", &LPI);
3681 Assert(isa<ConstantArray>(Clause) || isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(Clause),
3682 "Filter operand is not an array of constants!", &LPI);
3683 }
3684 }
3685
3686 visitInstruction(LPI);
3687}

3689void Verifier::visitResumeInst(ResumeInst &RI) {
3690 Assert(RI.getFunction()->hasPersonalityFn(),
3691 "ResumeInst needs to be in a function with a personality.", &RI);
3692
3693 if (!LandingPadResultTy)
3694 LandingPadResultTy = RI.getValue()->getType();
3695 else
3696 Assert(LandingPadResultTy == RI.getValue()->getType(),
3697 "The resume instruction should have a consistent result type "
3698 "inside a function.",
3699 &RI);
3700
3701 visitTerminator(RI);
3702}

3752
3753void Verifier::visitFuncletPadInst(FuncletPadInst &FPI) {
3754 User *FirstUser = nullptr;
3755 Value *FirstUnwindPad = nullptr;
3756 SmallVector<FuncletPadInst *, 8> Worklist({&FPI});
3757 SmallSet<FuncletPadInst *, 8> Seen;
3758
3759 while (!Worklist.empty()) {
3760 FuncletPadInst *CurrentPad = Worklist.pop_back_val();
3761 Assert(Seen.insert(CurrentPad).second,
3762 "FuncletPadInst must not be nested within itself", CurrentPad);
3763 Value *UnresolvedAncestorPad = nullptr;
3764 for (User *U : CurrentPad->users()) {
3765 BasicBlock *UnwindDest;
3766 if (auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(U)) {
3767 UnwindDest = CRI->getUnwindDest();
3768 } else if (auto *CSI = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(U)) {
3769 // We allow catchswitch unwind to caller to nest
3770 // within an outer pad that unwinds somewhere else,
3771 // because catchswitch doesn't have a nounwind variant.
3772 // See e.g. SimplifyCFGOpt::SimplifyUnreachable.
3773 if (CSI->unwindsToCaller())
3774 continue;
3775 UnwindDest = CSI->getUnwindDest();
3776 } else if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(U)) {
3777 UnwindDest = II->getUnwindDest();
3778 } else if (isa<CallInst>(U)) {
3779 // Calls which don't unwind may be found inside funclet
3780 // pads that unwind somewhere else. We don't *require*
3781 // such calls to be annotated nounwind.
3782 continue;
3783 } else if (auto *CPI = dyn_cast<CleanupPadInst>(U)) {
3784 // The unwind dest for a cleanup can only be found by
3785 // recursive search. Add it to the worklist, and we'll
3786 // search for its first use that determines where it unwinds.
3787 Worklist.push_back(CPI);
3788 continue;
3789 } else {
3790 Assert(isa<CatchReturnInst>(U), "Bogus funclet pad use", U);
3791 continue;
3792 }
3793
3794 Value *UnwindPad;
3795 bool ExitsFPI;
3796 if (UnwindDest) {
3797 UnwindPad = UnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI();
3798 if (!cast<Instruction>(UnwindPad)->isEHPad())
3799 continue;
3800 Value *UnwindParent = getParentPad(UnwindPad);
3801 // Ignore unwind edges that don't exit CurrentPad.
3802 if (UnwindParent == CurrentPad)
3803 continue;
3804 // Determine whether the original funclet pad is exited,
3805 // and if we are scanning nested pads determine how many
3806 // of them are exited so we can stop searching their
3807 // children.
3808 Value *ExitedPad = CurrentPad;
3809 ExitsFPI = false;
3810 do {
3811 if (ExitedPad == &FPI) {
3812 ExitsFPI = true;
3813 // Now we can resolve any ancestors of CurrentPad up to
3814 // FPI, but not including FPI since we need to make sure
3815 // to check all direct users of FPI for consistency.
3816 UnresolvedAncestorPad = &FPI;
3817 break;
3818 }
3819 Value *ExitedParent = getParentPad(ExitedPad);
3820 if (ExitedParent == UnwindParent) {
3821 // ExitedPad is the ancestor-most pad which this unwind
3822 // edge exits, so we can resolve up to it, meaning that
3823 // ExitedParent is the first ancestor still unresolved.
3824 UnresolvedAncestorPad = ExitedParent;
3825 break;
3826 }
3827 ExitedPad = ExitedParent;
3828 } while (!isa<ConstantTokenNone>(ExitedPad));
3829 } else {
3830 // Unwinding to caller exits all pads.
3831 UnwindPad = ConstantTokenNone::get(FPI.getContext());
3832 ExitsFPI = true;
3833 UnresolvedAncestorPad = &FPI;
3834 }
3835
3836 if (ExitsFPI) {
3837 // This unwind edge exits FPI. Make sure it agrees with other
3838 // such edges.
3839 if (FirstUser) {
3840 Assert(UnwindPad == FirstUnwindPad, "Unwind edges out of a funclet "
3841 "pad must have the same unwind "
3842 "dest",
3843 &FPI, U, FirstUser);
3844 } else {
3845 FirstUser = U;
3846 FirstUnwindPad = UnwindPad;
3847 // Record cleanup sibling unwinds for verifySiblingFuncletUnwinds
3848 if (isa<CleanupPadInst>(&FPI) && !isa<ConstantTokenNone>(UnwindPad) &&
3849 getParentPad(UnwindPad) == getParentPad(&FPI))
3850 SiblingFuncletInfo[&FPI] = cast<Instruction>(U);
3851 }
3852 }
3853 // Make sure we visit all uses of FPI, but for nested pads stop as
3854 // soon as we know where they unwind to.
3855 if (CurrentPad != &FPI)
3856 break;
3857 }
3858 if (UnresolvedAncestorPad) {
3859 if (CurrentPad == UnresolvedAncestorPad) {
3860 // When CurrentPad is FPI itself, we don't mark it as resolved even if
3861 // we've found an unwind edge that exits it, because we need to verify
3862 // all direct uses of FPI.
3863 assert(CurrentPad == &FPI);
3864 continue;
3865 }
3866 // Pop off the worklist any nested pads that we've found an unwind
3867 // destination for. The pads on the worklist are the uncles,
3868 // great-uncles, etc. of CurrentPad. We've found an unwind destination
3869 // for all ancestors of CurrentPad up to but not including
3870 // UnresolvedAncestorPad.
3871 Value *ResolvedPad = CurrentPad;
3872 while (!Worklist.empty()) {
3873 Value *UnclePad = Worklist.back();
3874 Value *AncestorPad = getParentPad(UnclePad);
3875 // Walk ResolvedPad up the ancestor list until we either find the
3876 // uncle's parent or the last resolved ancestor.
3877 while (ResolvedPad != AncestorPad) {
3878 Value *ResolvedParent = getParentPad(ResolvedPad);
3879 if (ResolvedParent == UnresolvedAncestorPad) {
3880 break;
3881 }
3882 ResolvedPad = ResolvedParent;
3883 }
3884 // If the resolved ancestor search didn't find the uncle's parent,
3885 // then the uncle is not yet resolved.
3886 if (ResolvedPad != AncestorPad)
3887 break;
3888 // This uncle is resolved, so pop it from the worklist.
3889 Worklist.pop_back();
3890 }
3891 }
3892 }
3893
3894 if (FirstUnwindPad) {
3895 if (auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(FPI.getParentPad())) {
3896 BasicBlock *SwitchUnwindDest = CatchSwitch->getUnwindDest();
3897 Value *SwitchUnwindPad;
3898 if (SwitchUnwindDest)
3899 SwitchUnwindPad = SwitchUnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI();
3900 else
3901 SwitchUnwindPad = ConstantTokenNone::get(FPI.getContext());
3902 Assert(SwitchUnwindPad == FirstUnwindPad,
3903 "Unwind edges out of a catch must have the same unwind dest as "
3904 "the parent catchswitch",
3905 &FPI, FirstUser, CatchSwitch);
3906 }
3907 }
3908
3909 visitInstruction(FPI);
3910}
3911
3912void Verifier::visitCatchSwitchInst(CatchSwitchInst &CatchSwitch) {
3913 BasicBlock *BB = CatchSwitch.getParent();
3914
3915 Function *F = BB->getParent();
3916 Assert(F->hasPersonalityFn(),
3917 "CatchSwitchInst needs to be in a function with a personality.",
3918 &CatchSwitch);
3919
3920 // The catchswitch instruction must be the first non-PHI instruction in the
3921 // block.
3922 Assert(BB->getFirstNonPHI() == &CatchSwitch,
3923 "CatchSwitchInst not the first non-PHI instruction in the block.",
3924 &CatchSwitch);
3925
3926 auto *ParentPad = CatchSwitch.getParentPad();
3927 Assert(isa<ConstantTokenNone>(ParentPad) || isa<FuncletPadInst>(ParentPad),
3928 "CatchSwitchInst has an invalid parent.", ParentPad);
3929
3930 if (BasicBlock *UnwindDest = CatchSwitch.getUnwindDest()) {
3931 Instruction *I = UnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI();
3932 Assert(I->isEHPad() && !isa<LandingPadInst>(I),
3933 "CatchSwitchInst must unwind to an EH block which is not a "
3934 "landingpad.",
3935 &CatchSwitch);
3936
3937 // Record catchswitch sibling unwinds for verifySiblingFuncletUnwinds
3938 if (getParentPad(I) == ParentPad)
3939 SiblingFuncletInfo[&CatchSwitch] = &CatchSwitch;
3940 }
3941
3942 Assert(CatchSwitch.getNumHandlers() != 0,
3943 "CatchSwitchInst cannot have empty handler list", &CatchSwitch);
3944
3945 for (BasicBlock *Handler : CatchSwitch.handlers()) {
3946 Assert(isa<CatchPadInst>(Handler->getFirstNonPHI()),
3947 "CatchSwitchInst handlers must be catchpads", &CatchSwitch, Handler);
3948 }
3949
3950 visitEHPadPredecessors(CatchSwitch);
3951 visitTerminator(CatchSwitch);
3952}

3954void Verifier::visitCleanupReturnInst(CleanupReturnInst &CRI) {

3956 "CleanupReturnInst needs to be provided a CleanupPad", &CRI,
3957 CRI.getOperand(0));
3958
3959 if (BasicBlock *UnwindDest = CRI.getUnwindDest()) {
3960 Instruction *I = UnwindDest->getFirstNonPHI();
3961 Assert(I->isEHPad() && !isa<LandingPadInst>(I),
3962 "CleanupReturnInst must unwind to an EH block which is not a "
3963 "landingpad.",
3964 &CRI);
3965 }
3966
3967 visitTerminator(CRI);

3969
3970void Verifier::verifyDominatesUse(Instruction &I, unsigned i) {
3971 Instruction *Op = cast<Instruction>(I.getOperand(i));
3972 // If the we have an invalid invoke, don't try to compute the dominance.
3973 // We already reject it in the invoke specific checks and the dominance
3974 // computation doesn't handle multiple edges.
3975 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Op)) {
3976 if (II->getNormalDest() == II->getUnwindDest())
3977 return;
3978 }
3979
3980 // Quick check whether the def has already been encountered in the same block.
3981 // PHI nodes are not checked to prevent accepting preceding PHIs, because PHI
3982 // uses are defined to happen on the incoming edge, not at the instruction.
3983 //
3984 // FIXME: If this operand is a MetadataAsValue (wrapping a LocalAsMetadata)
3985 // wrapping an SSA value, assert that we've already encountered it. See
3986 // related FIXME in Mapper::mapLocalAsMetadata in ValueMapper.cpp.
3987 if (!isa<PHINode>(I) && InstsInThisBlock.count(Op))
3988 return;
3989
3990 const Use &U = I.getOperandUse(i);
3991 Assert(DT.dominates(Op, U),
3992 "Instruction does not dominate all uses!", Op, &I);
3993}
3994
3995void Verifier::visitDereferenceableMetadata(Instruction& I, MDNode* MD) {
3996 Assert(I.getType()->isPointerTy(), "dereferenceable, dereferenceable_or_null "
3997 "apply only to pointer types", &I);
3998 Assert(isa<LoadInst>(I),
3999 "dereferenceable, dereferenceable_or_null apply only to load"
4000 " instructions, use attributes for calls or invokes", &I);
4001 Assert(MD->getNumOperands() == 1, "dereferenceable, dereferenceable_or_null "
4002 "take one operand!", &I);
4003 ConstantInt *CI = mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(MD->getOperand(0));
4004 Assert(CI && CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(64), "dereferenceable, "
4005 "dereferenceable_or_null metadata value must be an i64!", &I);
4006}
4007
4008/// verifyInstruction - Verify that an instruction is well formed.
4009///
4010void Verifier::visitInstruction(Instruction &I) {
4011 BasicBlock *BB = I.getParent();
4012 Assert(BB, "Instruction not embedded in basic block!", &I);
4013
4014 if (!isa<PHINode>(I)) { // Check that non-phi nodes are not self referential
4015 for (User *U : I.users()) {
4016 Assert(U != (User *)&I || !DT.isReachableFromEntry(BB),
4017 "Only PHI nodes may reference their own value!", &I);
4018 }
4019 }
4020
4021 // Check that void typed values don't have names
4022 Assert(!I.getType()->isVoidTy() || !I.hasName(),
4023 "Instruction has a name, but provides a void value!", &I);
4024
4025 // Check that the return value of the instruction is either void or a legal
4026 // value type.
4027 Assert(I.getType()->isVoidTy() || I.getType()->isFirstClassType(),
4028 "Instruction returns a non-scalar type!", &I);
4029
4030 // Check that the instruction doesn't produce metadata. Calls are already
4031 // checked against the callee type.
4032 Assert(!I.getType()->isMetadataTy() || isa<CallInst>(I) || isa<InvokeInst>(I),
4033 "Invalid use of metadata!", &I);
4034
4035 // Check that all uses of the instruction, if they are instructions
4036 // themselves, actually have parent basic blocks. If the use is not an
4037 // instruction, it is an error!
4038 for (Use &U : I.uses()) {
4039 if (Instruction *Used = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U.getUser()))
4040 Assert(Used->getParent() != nullptr,
4041 "Instruction referencing"
4042 " instruction not embedded in a basic block!",
4043 &I, Used);
4044 else {
4045 CheckFailed("Use of instruction is not an instruction!", U);
4046 return;
4047 }
4048 }
4049
4050 // Get a pointer to the call base of the instruction if it is some form of
4051 // call.
4052 const CallBase *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I);
4053
4054 for (unsigned i = 0, e = I.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
4055 Assert(I.getOperand(i) != nullptr, "Instruction has null operand!", &I);
4056
4057 // Check to make sure that only first-class-values are operands to
4058 // instructions.
4059 if (!I.getOperand(i)->getType()->isFirstClassType()) {
4060 Assert(false, "Instruction operands must be first-class values!", &I);
4061 }
4062
4063 if (Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4064 // Check to make sure that the "address of" an intrinsic function is never
4065 // taken.
4066 Assert(!F->isIntrinsic() ||
4067 (CBI && &CBI->getCalledOperandUse() == &I.getOperandUse(i)),
4068 "Cannot take the address of an intrinsic!", &I);
4069 Assert(
4070 !F->isIntrinsic() || isa<CallInst>(I) ||
4071 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::donothing ||
4072 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::coro_resume ||
4073 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::coro_destroy ||
4074 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_patchpoint_void ||
4075 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_patchpoint_i64 ||
4076 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint ||
4077 F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::wasm_rethrow_in_catch,
4078 "Cannot invoke an intrinsic other than donothing, patchpoint, "
4079 "statepoint, coro_resume or coro_destroy",
4080 &I);
4081 Assert(F->getParent() == &M, "Referencing function in another module!",
4082 &I, &M, F, F->getParent());
4083 } else if (BasicBlock *OpBB = dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4084 Assert(OpBB->getParent() == BB->getParent(),
4085 "Referring to a basic block in another function!", &I);
4086 } else if (Argument *OpArg = dyn_cast<Argument>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4087 Assert(OpArg->getParent() == BB->getParent(),
4088 "Referring to an argument in another function!", &I);
4089 } else if (GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4090 Assert(GV->getParent() == &M, "Referencing global in another module!", &I,
4091 &M, GV, GV->getParent());
4092 } else if (isa<Instruction>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4093 verifyDominatesUse(I, i);
4094 } else if (isa<InlineAsm>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4095 Assert(CBI && &CBI->getCalledOperandUse() == &I.getOperandUse(i),
4096 "Cannot take the address of an inline asm!", &I);
4097 } else if (ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(I.getOperand(i))) {
4098 if (CE->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy() ||
4099 !DL.getNonIntegralAddressSpaces().empty()) {
4100 // If we have a ConstantExpr pointer, we need to see if it came from an
4101 // illegal bitcast. If the datalayout string specifies non-integral
4102 // address spaces then we also need to check for illegal ptrtoint and
4103 // inttoptr expressions.
4104 visitConstantExprsRecursively(CE);
4105 }
4106 }
4107 }
4108
4109 if (MDNode *MD = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_fpmath)) {
4110 Assert(I.getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy(),
4111 "fpmath requires a floating point result!", &I);
4112 Assert(MD->getNumOperands() == 1, "fpmath takes one operand!", &I);
4113 if (ConstantFP *CFP0 =
4114 mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantFP>(MD->getOperand(0))) {
4115 const APFloat &Accuracy = CFP0->getValueAPF();
4116 Assert(&Accuracy.getSemantics() == &APFloat::IEEEsingle(),
4117 "fpmath accuracy must have float type", &I);
4118 Assert(Accuracy.isFiniteNonZero() && !Accuracy.isNegative(),
4119 "fpmath accuracy not a positive number!", &I);
4120 } else {
4121 Assert(false, "invalid fpmath accuracy!", &I);
4122 }
4123 }
4124
4125 if (MDNode *Range = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range)) {
4126 Assert(isa<LoadInst>(I) || isa<CallInst>(I) || isa<InvokeInst>(I),
4127 "Ranges are only for loads, calls and invokes!", &I);
4128 visitRangeMetadata(I, Range, I.getType());
4129 }
4130
4131 if (I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_nonnull)) {
4132 Assert(I.getType()->isPointerTy(), "nonnull applies only to pointer types",
4133 &I);
4134 Assert(isa<LoadInst>(I),
4135 "nonnull applies only to load instructions, use attributes"
4136 " for calls or invokes",
4137 &I);
4138 }
4139
4140 if (MDNode *MD = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable))
4141 visitDereferenceableMetadata(I, MD);
4142
4143 if (MDNode *MD = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable_or_null))
4144 visitDereferenceableMetadata(I, MD);
4145
4146 if (MDNode *TBAA = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_tbaa))
4147 TBAAVerifyHelper.visitTBAAMetadata(I, TBAA);
4148
4149 if (MDNode *AlignMD = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_align)) {
4150 Assert(I.getType()->isPointerTy(), "align applies only to pointer types",
4151 &I);
4152 Assert(isa<LoadInst>(I), "align applies only to load instructions, "
4153 "use attributes for calls or invokes", &I);
4154 Assert(AlignMD->getNumOperands() == 1, "align takes one operand!", &I);
4155 ConstantInt *CI = mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(AlignMD->getOperand(0));
4156 Assert(CI && CI->getType()->isIntegerTy(64),
4157 "align metadata value must be an i64!", &I);
4158 uint64_t Align = CI->getZExtValue();
4159 Assert(isPowerOf2_64(Align),
4160 "align metadata value must be a power of 2!", &I);
4161 Assert(Align <= Value::MaximumAlignment,
4162 "alignment is larger that implementation defined limit", &I);
4163 }
4164
4165 if (MDNode *N = I.getDebugLoc().getAsMDNode()) {
4166 AssertDI(isa<DILocation>(N), "invalid !dbg metadata attachment", &I, N);
4167 visitMDNode(*N);
4168 }
4169
4170 if (auto *DII = dyn_cast<DbgVariableIntrinsic>(&I))
4171 verifyFragmentExpression(*DII);
4172
4173 InstsInThisBlock.insert(&I);
4174}
4175
4176/// Allow intrinsics to be verified in different ways.
4177void Verifier::visitIntrinsicCall(Intrinsic::ID ID, CallBase &Call) {
4178 Function *IF = Call.getCalledFunction();
4179 Assert(IF->isDeclaration(), "Intrinsic functions should never be defined!",
4180 IF);
4181
4182 // Verify that the intrinsic prototype lines up with what the .td files
4183 // describe.
4184 FunctionType *IFTy = IF->getFunctionType();
4185 bool IsVarArg = IFTy->isVarArg();
4186
4187 SmallVector<Intrinsic::IITDescriptor, 8> Table;
4188 getIntrinsicInfoTableEntries(ID, Table);
4189 ArrayRef<Intrinsic::IITDescriptor> TableRef = Table;
4190
4191 // Walk the descriptors to extract overloaded types.
4192 SmallVector<Type *, 4> ArgTys;
4193 Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypesResult Res =
4194 Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicSignature(IFTy, TableRef, ArgTys);
4195 Assert(Res != Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchRet,
4196 "Intrinsic has incorrect return type!", IF);
4197 Assert(Res != Intrinsic::MatchIntrinsicTypes_NoMatchArg,
4198 "Intrinsic has incorrect argument type!", IF);
4199
4200 // Verify if the intrinsic call matches the vararg property.
4201 if (IsVarArg)
4202 Assert(!Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicVarArg(IsVarArg, TableRef),
4203 "Intrinsic was not defined with variable arguments!", IF);
4204 else
4205 Assert(!Intrinsic::matchIntrinsicVarArg(IsVarArg, TableRef),
4206 "Callsite was not defined with variable arguments!", IF);
4207
4208 // All descriptors should be absorbed by now.
4209 Assert(TableRef.empty(), "Intrinsic has too few arguments!", IF);
4210
4211 // Now that we have the intrinsic ID and the actual argument types (and we
4212 // know they are legal for the intrinsic!) get the intrinsic name through the
4213 // usual means. This allows us to verify the mangling of argument types into
4214 // the name.
4215 const std::string ExpectedName = Intrinsic::getName(ID, ArgTys);
4216 Assert(ExpectedName == IF->getName(),
4217 "Intrinsic name not mangled correctly for type arguments! "
4218 "Should be: " +
4219 ExpectedName,
4220 IF);
4221
4222 // If the intrinsic takes MDNode arguments, verify that they are either global
4223 // or are local to *this* function.
4224 for (Value *V : Call.args())
4225 if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<MetadataAsValue>(V))
4226 visitMetadataAsValue(*MD, Call.getCaller());
4227
4228 switch (ID) {
4229 default:
4230 break;
4231 case Intrinsic::coro_id: {
4232 auto *InfoArg = Call.getArgOperand(3)->stripPointerCasts();
4233 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(InfoArg))
4234 break;
4235 auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(InfoArg);
4236 Assert(GV && GV->isConstant() && GV->hasDefinitiveInitializer(),
4237 "info argument of llvm.coro.begin must refer to an initialized "
4238 "constant");
4239 Constant *Init = GV->getInitializer();
4240 Assert(isa<ConstantStruct>(Init) || isa<ConstantArray>(Init),
4241 "info argument of llvm.coro.begin must refer to either a struct or "
4242 "an array");
4243 break;
4244 }
4245 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fadd:
4246 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fsub:
4247 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul:
4248 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fdiv:
4249 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_frem:
4250 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma:
4251 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fptrunc:
4252 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fpext:
4253 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sqrt:
4254 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_pow:
4255 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_powi:
4256 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sin:
4257 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_cos:
4258 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_exp:
4259 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_exp2:
4260 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log:
4261 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log10:
4262 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log2:
4263 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint:
4264 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_nearbyint:
4265 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_maxnum:
4266 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_minnum:
4267 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ceil:
4268 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_floor:
4269 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_round:
4270 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_trunc:
4271 visitConstrainedFPIntrinsic(cast<ConstrainedFPIntrinsic>(Call));
4272 break;
4273 case Intrinsic::dbg_declare: // llvm.dbg.declare
4274 Assert(isa<MetadataAsValue>(Call.getArgOperand(0)),
4275 "invalid llvm.dbg.declare intrinsic call 1", Call);
4276 visitDbgIntrinsic("declare", cast<DbgVariableIntrinsic>(Call));
4277 break;
4278 case Intrinsic::dbg_addr: // llvm.dbg.addr
4279 visitDbgIntrinsic("addr", cast<DbgVariableIntrinsic>(Call));
4280 break;
4281 case Intrinsic::dbg_value: // llvm.dbg.value
4282 visitDbgIntrinsic("value", cast<DbgVariableIntrinsic>(Call));
4283 break;
4284 case Intrinsic::dbg_label: // llvm.dbg.label
4285 visitDbgLabelIntrinsic("label", cast<DbgLabelInst>(Call));
4286 break;
4287 case Intrinsic::memcpy:
4288 case Intrinsic::memmove:
4289 case Intrinsic::memset: {
4290 const auto *MI = cast<MemIntrinsic>(&Call);
4291 auto IsValidAlignment = [&](unsigned Alignment) -> bool {
4292 return Alignment == 0 || isPowerOf2_32(Alignment);
4293 };
4294 Assert(IsValidAlignment(MI->getDestAlignment()),
4295 "alignment of arg 0 of memory intrinsic must be 0 or a power of 2",
4296 Call);
4297 if (const auto *MTI = dyn_cast<MemTransferInst>(MI)) {
4298 Assert(IsValidAlignment(MTI->getSourceAlignment()),
4299 "alignment of arg 1 of memory intrinsic must be 0 or a power of 2",
4300 Call);
4301 }
4302
4303 break;
4304 }
4305 case Intrinsic::memcpy_element_unordered_atomic:
4306 case Intrinsic::memmove_element_unordered_atomic:
4307 case Intrinsic::memset_element_unordered_atomic: {
4308 const auto *AMI = cast<AtomicMemIntrinsic>(&Call);
4309
4310 ConstantInt *ElementSizeCI =
4311 cast<ConstantInt>(AMI->getRawElementSizeInBytes());
4312 const APInt &ElementSizeVal = ElementSizeCI->getValue();
4313 Assert(ElementSizeVal.isPowerOf2(),
4314 "element size of the element-wise atomic memory intrinsic "
4315 "must be a power of 2",
4316 Call);
4317
4318 if (auto *LengthCI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(AMI->getLength())) {
4319 uint64_t Length = LengthCI->getZExtValue();
4320 uint64_t ElementSize = AMI->getElementSizeInBytes();
4321 Assert((Length % ElementSize) == 0,
4322 "constant length must be a multiple of the element size in the "
4323 "element-wise atomic memory intrinsic",
4324 Call);
4325 }
4326
4327 auto IsValidAlignment = [&](uint64_t Alignment) {
4328 return isPowerOf2_64(Alignment) && ElementSizeVal.ule(Alignment);
4329 };
4330 uint64_t DstAlignment = AMI->getDestAlignment();
4331 Assert(IsValidAlignment(DstAlignment),
4332 "incorrect alignment of the destination argument", Call);
4333 if (const auto *AMT = dyn_cast<AtomicMemTransferInst>(AMI)) {
4334 uint64_t SrcAlignment = AMT->getSourceAlignment();
4335 Assert(IsValidAlignment(SrcAlignment),
4336 "incorrect alignment of the source argument", Call);
4337 }
4338 break;
4339 }
4340 case Intrinsic::gcroot:
4341 case Intrinsic::gcwrite:
4342 case Intrinsic::gcread:
4343 if (ID == Intrinsic::gcroot) {
4344 AllocaInst *AI =
4345 dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(Call.getArgOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts());
4346 Assert(AI, "llvm.gcroot parameter #1 must be an alloca.", Call);
4347 Assert(isa<Constant>(Call.getArgOperand(1)),
4348 "llvm.gcroot parameter #2 must be a constant.", Call);
4349 if (!AI->getAllocatedType()->isPointerTy()) {
4350 Assert(!isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Call.getArgOperand(1)),
4351 "llvm.gcroot parameter #1 must either be a pointer alloca, "
4352 "or argument #2 must be a non-null constant.",
4353 Call);
4354 }
4355 }
4356
4357 Assert(Call.getParent()->getParent()->hasGC(),
4358 "Enclosing function does not use GC.", Call);
4359 break;
4360 case Intrinsic::init_trampoline:
4361 Assert(isa<Function>(Call.getArgOperand(1)->stripPointerCasts()),
4362 "llvm.init_trampoline parameter #2 must resolve to a function.",
4363 Call);
4364 break;
4365 case Intrinsic::prefetch:
4366 Assert(cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(1))->getZExtValue() < 2 &&
4367 cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(2))->getZExtValue() < 4,
4368 "invalid arguments to llvm.prefetch", Call);
4369 break;
4370 case Intrinsic::stackprotector:
4371 Assert(isa<AllocaInst>(Call.getArgOperand(1)->stripPointerCasts()),
4372 "llvm.stackprotector parameter #2 must resolve to an alloca.", Call);
4373 break;
4374 case Intrinsic::localescape: {
4375 BasicBlock *BB = Call.getParent();
4376 Assert(BB == &BB->getParent()->front(),
4377 "llvm.localescape used outside of entry block", Call);
4378 Assert(!SawFrameEscape,
4379 "multiple calls to llvm.localescape in one function", Call);
4380 for (Value *Arg : Call.args()) {
4381 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Arg))
4382 continue; // Null values are allowed as placeholders.
4383 auto *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(Arg->stripPointerCasts());
4384 Assert(AI && AI->isStaticAlloca(),
4385 "llvm.localescape only accepts static allocas", Call);
4386 }
4387 FrameEscapeInfo[BB->getParent()].first = Call.getNumArgOperands();
4388 SawFrameEscape = true;
4389 break;
4390 }
4391 case Intrinsic::localrecover: {
4392 Value *FnArg = Call.getArgOperand(0)->stripPointerCasts();
4393 Function *Fn = dyn_cast<Function>(FnArg);
4394 Assert(Fn && !Fn->isDeclaration(),
4395 "llvm.localrecover first "
4396 "argument must be function defined in this module",
4397 Call);
4398 auto *IdxArg = cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(2));
4399 auto &Entry = FrameEscapeInfo[Fn];
4400 Entry.second = unsigned(
4401 std::max(uint64_t(Entry.second), IdxArg->getLimitedValue(~0U) + 1));
4402 break;
4403 }
4404
4405 case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint:
4406 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&Call))
4407 Assert(!CI->isInlineAsm(),
4408 "gc.statepoint support for inline assembly unimplemented", CI);
4409 Assert(Call.getParent()->getParent()->hasGC(),
4410 "Enclosing function does not use GC.", Call);
4411
4412 verifyStatepoint(Call);
4413 break;
4414 case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_result: {
4415 Assert(Call.getParent()->getParent()->hasGC(),
4416 "Enclosing function does not use GC.", Call);
4417 // Are we tied to a statepoint properly?
4418 const auto *StatepointCall = dyn_cast<CallBase>(Call.getArgOperand(0));
4419 const Function *StatepointFn =
4420 StatepointCall ? StatepointCall->getCalledFunction() : nullptr;
4421 Assert(StatepointFn && StatepointFn->isDeclaration() &&
4422 StatepointFn->getIntrinsicID() ==
4423 Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint,
4424 "gc.result operand #1 must be from a statepoint", Call,
4425 Call.getArgOperand(0));
4426
4427 // Assert that result type matches wrapped callee.
4428 const Value *Target = StatepointCall->getArgOperand(2);
4429 auto *PT = cast<PointerType>(Target->getType());
4430 auto *TargetFuncType = cast<FunctionType>(PT->getElementType());
4431 Assert(Call.getType() == TargetFuncType->getReturnType(),
4432 "gc.result result type does not match wrapped callee", Call);
4433 break;
4434 }
4435 case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_relocate: {
4436 Assert(Call.getNumArgOperands() == 3, "wrong number of arguments", Call);
4437
4438 Assert(isa<PointerType>(Call.getType()->getScalarType()),
4439 "gc.relocate must return a pointer or a vector of pointers", Call);
4440
4441 // Check that this relocate is correctly tied to the statepoint
4442
4443 // This is case for relocate on the unwinding path of an invoke statepoint
4444 if (LandingPadInst *LandingPad =
4445 dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(Call.getArgOperand(0))) {
4446
4447 const BasicBlock *InvokeBB =
4448 LandingPad->getParent()->getUniquePredecessor();
4449
4450 // Landingpad relocates should have only one predecessor with invoke
4451 // statepoint terminator
4452 Assert(InvokeBB, "safepoints should have unique landingpads",
4453 LandingPad->getParent());
4454 Assert(InvokeBB->getTerminator(), "safepoint block should be well formed",
4455 InvokeBB);
4456 Assert(isStatepoint(InvokeBB->getTerminator()),
4457 "gc relocate should be linked to a statepoint", InvokeBB);
4458 } else {
4459 // In all other cases relocate should be tied to the statepoint directly.
4460 // This covers relocates on a normal return path of invoke statepoint and
4461 // relocates of a call statepoint.
4462 auto Token = Call.getArgOperand(0);
4463 Assert(isa<Instruction>(Token) && isStatepoint(cast<Instruction>(Token)),
4464 "gc relocate is incorrectly tied to the statepoint", Call, Token);
4465 }
4466
4467 // Verify rest of the relocate arguments.
4468 const CallBase &StatepointCall =
4469 *cast<CallBase>(cast<GCRelocateInst>(Call).getStatepoint());
4470
4471 // Both the base and derived must be piped through the safepoint.
4472 Value *Base = Call.getArgOperand(1);
4473 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(Base),
4474 "gc.relocate operand #2 must be integer offset", Call);
4475
4476 Value *Derived = Call.getArgOperand(2);
4477 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(Derived),
4478 "gc.relocate operand #3 must be integer offset", Call);
4479
4480 const int BaseIndex = cast<ConstantInt>(Base)->getZExtValue();
4481 const int DerivedIndex = cast<ConstantInt>(Derived)->getZExtValue();
4482 // Check the bounds
4483 Assert(0 <= BaseIndex && BaseIndex < (int)StatepointCall.arg_size(),
4484 "gc.relocate: statepoint base index out of bounds", Call);
4485 Assert(0 <= DerivedIndex && DerivedIndex < (int)StatepointCall.arg_size(),
4486 "gc.relocate: statepoint derived index out of bounds", Call);
4487
4488 // Check that BaseIndex and DerivedIndex fall within the 'gc parameters'
4489 // section of the statepoint's argument.
4490 Assert(StatepointCall.arg_size() > 0,
4491 "gc.statepoint: insufficient arguments");
4492 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(StatepointCall.getArgOperand(3)),
4493 "gc.statement: number of call arguments must be constant integer");
4494 const unsigned NumCallArgs =
4495 cast<ConstantInt>(StatepointCall.getArgOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
4496 Assert(StatepointCall.arg_size() > NumCallArgs + 5,
4497 "gc.statepoint: mismatch in number of call arguments");
4498 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(StatepointCall.getArgOperand(NumCallArgs + 5)),
4499 "gc.statepoint: number of transition arguments must be "
4500 "a constant integer");
4501 const int NumTransitionArgs =
4502 cast<ConstantInt>(StatepointCall.getArgOperand(NumCallArgs + 5))
4503 ->getZExtValue();
4504 const int DeoptArgsStart = 4 + NumCallArgs + 1 + NumTransitionArgs + 1;
4505 Assert(isa<ConstantInt>(StatepointCall.getArgOperand(DeoptArgsStart)),
4506 "gc.statepoint: number of deoptimization arguments must be "
4507 "a constant integer");
4508 const int NumDeoptArgs =
4509 cast<ConstantInt>(StatepointCall.getArgOperand(DeoptArgsStart))
4510 ->getZExtValue();
4511 const int GCParamArgsStart = DeoptArgsStart + 1 + NumDeoptArgs;
4512 const int GCParamArgsEnd = StatepointCall.arg_size();
4513 Assert(GCParamArgsStart <= BaseIndex && BaseIndex < GCParamArgsEnd,
4514 "gc.relocate: statepoint base index doesn't fall within the "
4515 "'gc parameters' section of the statepoint call",
4516 Call);
4517 Assert(GCParamArgsStart <= DerivedIndex && DerivedIndex < GCParamArgsEnd,
4518 "gc.relocate: statepoint derived index doesn't fall within the "
4519 "'gc parameters' section of the statepoint call",
4520 Call);
4521
4522 // Relocated value must be either a pointer type or vector-of-pointer type,
4523 // but gc_relocate does not need to return the same pointer type as the
4524 // relocated pointer. It can be casted to the correct type later if it's
4525 // desired. However, they must have the same address space and 'vectorness'
4526 GCRelocateInst &Relocate = cast<GCRelocateInst>(Call);
4527 Assert(Relocate.getDerivedPtr()->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy(),
4528 "gc.relocate: relocated value must be a gc pointer", Call);
4529
4530 auto ResultType = Call.getType();
4531 auto DerivedType = Relocate.getDerivedPtr()->getType();
4532 Assert(ResultType->isVectorTy() == DerivedType->isVectorTy(),
4533 "gc.relocate: vector relocates to vector and pointer to pointer",
4534 Call);
4535 Assert(
4536 ResultType->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
4537 DerivedType->getPointerAddressSpace(),
4538 "gc.relocate: relocating a pointer shouldn't change its address space",
4539 Call);
4540 break;
4541 }
4542 case Intrinsic::eh_exceptioncode:
4543 case Intrinsic::eh_exceptionpointer: {
4544 Assert(isa<CatchPadInst>(Call.getArgOperand(0)),
4545 "eh.exceptionpointer argument must be a catchpad", Call);
4546 break;
4547 }
4548 case Intrinsic::masked_load: {
4549 Assert(Call.getType()->isVectorTy(), "masked_load: must return a vector",
4550 Call);
4551
4552 Value *Ptr = Call.getArgOperand(0);
4553 ConstantInt *Alignment = cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(1));
4554 Value *Mask = Call.getArgOperand(2);
4555 Value *PassThru = Call.getArgOperand(3);
4556 Assert(Mask->getType()->isVectorTy(), "masked_load: mask must be vector",
4557 Call);
4558 Assert(Alignment->getValue().isPowerOf2(),
4559 "masked_load: alignment must be a power of 2", Call);
4560
4561 // DataTy is the overloaded type
4562 Type *DataTy = cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())->getElementType();
4563 Assert(DataTy == Call.getType(),
4564 "masked_load: return must match pointer type", Call);
4565 Assert(PassThru->getType() == DataTy,
4566 "masked_load: pass through and data type must match", Call);
4567 Assert(Mask->getType()->getVectorNumElements() ==
4568 DataTy->getVectorNumElements(),
4569 "masked_load: vector mask must be same length as data", Call);
4570 break;
4571 }
4572 case Intrinsic::masked_store: {
4573 Value *Val = Call.getArgOperand(0);
4574 Value *Ptr = Call.getArgOperand(1);
4575 ConstantInt *Alignment = cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(2));
4576 Value *Mask = Call.getArgOperand(3);
4577 Assert(Mask->getType()->isVectorTy(), "masked_store: mask must be vector",
4578 Call);
4579 Assert(Alignment->getValue().isPowerOf2(),
4580 "masked_store: alignment must be a power of 2", Call);
4581
4582 // DataTy is the overloaded type
4583 Type *DataTy = cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())->getElementType();
4584 Assert(DataTy == Val->getType(),
4585 "masked_store: storee must match pointer type", Call);
4586 Assert(Mask->getType()->getVectorNumElements() ==
4587 DataTy->getVectorNumElements(),
4588 "masked_store: vector mask must be same length as data", Call);
4589 break;
4590 }
4591
4592 case Intrinsic::experimental_guard: {
4593 Assert(isa<CallInst>(Call), "experimental_guard cannot be invoked", Call);
4594 Assert(Call.countOperandBundlesOfType(LLVMContext::OB_deopt) == 1,
4595 "experimental_guard must have exactly one "
4596 "\"deopt\" operand bundle");
4597 break;
4598 }
4599
4600 case Intrinsic::vastart:
4601 case Intrinsic::vacopy:
4602 case Intrinsic::vaend: {
4603 Assert(isa<CallInst>(Call),
4604 "variadic argument intrinsics cannot be invoked", Call);
4605 Value *Val = Call.getArgOperand(0);
4606 Assert(Val->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() == DL.getAllocaAddrSpace(),
4607 "variadic argument intrinsics must be in alloca address space",
4608 Call);
4609 break;
4610 }
4611
4612 case Intrinsic::experimental_deoptimize: {
4613 Assert(isa<CallInst>(Call), "experimental_deoptimize cannot be invoked",
4614 Call);
4615 Assert(Call.countOperandBundlesOfType(LLVMContext::OB_deopt) == 1,
4616 "experimental_deoptimize must have exactly one "
4617 "\"deopt\" operand bundle");
4618 Assert(Call.getType() == Call.getFunction()->getReturnType(),
4619 "experimental_deoptimize return type must match caller return type");
4620
4621 if (isa<CallInst>(Call)) {
4622 auto *RI = dyn_cast<ReturnInst>(Call.getNextNode());
4623 Assert(RI,
4624 "calls to experimental_deoptimize must be followed by a return");
4625
4626 if (!Call.getType()->isVoidTy() && RI)
4627 Assert(RI->getReturnValue() == &Call,
4628 "calls to experimental_deoptimize must be followed by a return "
4629 "of the value computed by experimental_deoptimize");
4630 }
4631
4632 break;
4633 }
4634 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
4635 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
4636 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
4637 case Intrinsic::usub_sat: {
4638 Value *Op1 = Call.getArgOperand(0);
4639 Value *Op2 = Call.getArgOperand(1);
4640 Assert(Op1->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
4641 "first operand of [us][add|sub]_sat must be an int type or vector "
4642 "of ints");
4643 Assert(Op2->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
4644 "second operand of [us][add|sub]_sat must be an int type or vector "
4645 "of ints");
4646 break;
4647 }
4648 case Intrinsic::smul_fix:
4649 case Intrinsic::smul_fix_sat:
4650 case Intrinsic::umul_fix: {
4651 Value *Op1 = Call.getArgOperand(0);
4652 Value *Op2 = Call.getArgOperand(1);
4653 Assert(Op1->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
4654 "first operand of [us]mul_fix[_sat] must be an int type or vector "
4655 "of ints");
4656 Assert(Op2->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(),
4657 "second operand of [us]mul_fix_[sat] must be an int type or vector "
4658 "of ints");
4659
4660 auto *Op3 = cast<ConstantInt>(Call.getArgOperand(2));
4661 Assert(Op3->getType()->getBitWidth() <= 32,
4662 "third argument of [us]mul_fix[_sat] must fit within 32 bits");
4663
4664 if (ID == Intrinsic::smul_fix || ID == Intrinsic::smul_fix_sat) {
4665 Assert(
4666 Op3->getZExtValue() < Op1->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(),
4667 "the scale of smul_fix[_sat] must be less than the width of the operands");
4668 } else {
4669 Assert(Op3->getZExtValue() <= Op1->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(),
4670 "the scale of umul_fix[_sat] must be less than or equal to the width of "
4671 "the operands");
4672 }
4673 break;
4674 }
4675 case Intrinsic::lround:
4676 case Intrinsic::llround:
4677 case Intrinsic::lrint:
4678 case Intrinsic::llrint: {
4679 Type *ValTy = Call.getArgOperand(0)->getType();
4680 Type *ResultTy = Call.getType();
4681 Assert(!ValTy->isVectorTy() && !ResultTy->isVectorTy(),
4682 "Intrinsic does not support vectors", &Call);
4683 break;
4684 }
4685 };
4686}
4687
4688/// Carefully grab the subprogram from a local scope.
4689///
4690/// This carefully grabs the subprogram from a local scope, avoiding the
4691/// built-in assertions that would typically fire.
4692static DISubprogram *getSubprogram(Metadata *LocalScope) {
4693 if (!LocalScope)
4694 return nullptr;
4695
4696 if (auto *SP = dyn_cast<DISubprogram>(LocalScope))
4697 return SP;
4698
4699 if (auto *LB = dyn_cast<DILexicalBlockBase>(LocalScope))
4700 return getSubprogram(LB->getRawScope());
4701
4702 // Just return null; broken scope chains are checked elsewhere.
4703 assert(!isa<DILocalScope>(LocalScope) && "Unknown type of local scope");
4704 return nullptr;
4705}
4706
4707void Verifier::visitConstrainedFPIntrinsic(ConstrainedFPIntrinsic &FPI) {
4708 unsigned NumOperands = FPI.getNumArgOperands();
4709 bool HasExceptionMD = false;
4710 bool HasRoundingMD = false;
4711 switch (FPI.getIntrinsicID()) {
4712 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sqrt:
4713 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_sin:
4714 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_cos:
4715 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_exp:
4716 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_exp2:
4717 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log:
4718 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log10:
4719 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_log2:
4720 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint:
4721 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_nearbyint:
4722 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ceil:
4723 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_floor:
4724 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_round:
4725 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_trunc:
4726 Assert((NumOperands == 3), "invalid arguments for constrained FP intrinsic",
4727 &FPI);
4728 HasExceptionMD = true;
4729 HasRoundingMD = true;
4730 break;
4731
4732 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fma:
4733 Assert((NumOperands == 5), "invalid arguments for constrained FP intrinsic",
4734 &FPI);
4735 HasExceptionMD = true;
4736 HasRoundingMD = true;
4737 break;
4738
4739 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fadd:
4740 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fsub:
4741 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul:
4742 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fdiv:
4743 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_frem:
4744 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_pow:
4745 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_powi:
4746 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_maxnum:
4747 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_minnum:
4748 Assert((NumOperands == 4), "invalid arguments for constrained FP intrinsic",
4749 &FPI);
4750 HasExceptionMD = true;
4751 HasRoundingMD = true;
4752 break;
4753
4754 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fptrunc:
4755 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fpext: {
4756 if (FPI.getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fptrunc) {
4757 Assert((NumOperands == 3),
4758 "invalid arguments for constrained FP intrinsic", &FPI);
4759 HasRoundingMD = true;
4760 } else {
4761 Assert((NumOperands == 2),
4762 "invalid arguments for constrained FP intrinsic", &FPI);
4763 }
4764 HasExceptionMD = true;
4765
4766 Value *Operand = FPI.getArgOperand(0);
4767 Type *OperandTy = Operand->getType();
4768 Value *Result = &FPI;
4769 Type *ResultTy = Result->getType();
4770 Assert(OperandTy->isFPOrFPVectorTy(),
4771 "Intrinsic first argument must be FP or FP vector", &FPI);
4772 Assert(ResultTy->isFPOrFPVectorTy(),
4773 "Intrinsic result must be FP or FP vector", &FPI);
4774 Assert(OperandTy->isVectorTy() == ResultTy->isVectorTy(),
4775 "Intrinsic first argument and result disagree on vector use", &FPI);
4776 if (OperandTy->isVectorTy()) {
4777 auto *OperandVecTy = cast<VectorType>(OperandTy);
4778 auto *ResultVecTy = cast<VectorType>(ResultTy);
4779 Assert(OperandVecTy->getNumElements() == ResultVecTy->getNumElements(),
4780 "Intrinsic first argument and result vector lengths must be equal",
4781 &FPI);
4782 }
4783 if (FPI.getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fptrunc) {
4784 Assert(OperandTy->getScalarSizeInBits() > ResultTy->getScalarSizeInBits(),
4785 "Intrinsic first argument's type must be larger than result type",
4786 &FPI);
4787 } else {
4788 Assert(OperandTy->getScalarSizeInBits() < ResultTy->getScalarSizeInBits(),
4789 "Intrinsic first argument's type must be smaller than result type",
4790 &FPI);
4791 }
4792 }
4793 break;
4794
4795 default:
4796 llvm_unreachable("Invalid constrained FP intrinsic!");
4797 }
4798
4799 // If a non-metadata argument is passed in a metadata slot then the
4800 // error will be caught earlier when the incorrect argument doesn't
4801 // match the specification in the intrinsic call table. Thus, no
4802 // argument type check is needed here.
4803
4804 if (HasExceptionMD) {
4805 Assert(FPI.getExceptionBehavior() != ConstrainedFPIntrinsic::ebInvalid,
4806 "invalid exception behavior argument", &FPI);
4807 }
4808 if (HasRoundingMD) {
4809 Assert(FPI.getRoundingMode() != ConstrainedFPIntrinsic::rmInvalid,
4810 "invalid rounding mode argument", &FPI);
4811 }
4812}
4813
4814void Verifier::visitDbgIntrinsic(StringRef Kind, DbgVariableIntrinsic &DII) {
4815 auto *MD = cast<MetadataAsValue>(DII.getArgOperand(0))->getMetadata();
4816 AssertDI(isa<ValueAsMetadata>(MD) ||
4817 (isa<MDNode>(MD) && !cast<MDNode>(MD)->getNumOperands()),
4818 "invalid llvm.dbg." + Kind + " intrinsic address/value", &DII, MD);
4819 AssertDI(isa<DILocalVariable>(DII.getRawVariable()),
4820 "invalid llvm.dbg." + Kind + " intrinsic variable", &DII,
4821 DII.getRawVariable());
4822 AssertDI(isa<DIExpression>(DII.getRawExpression()),
4823 "invalid llvm.dbg." + Kind + " intrinsic expression", &DII,
4824 DII.getRawExpression());
4825
4826 // Ignore broken !dbg attachments; they're checked elsewhere.
4827 if (MDNode *N = DII.getDebugLoc().getAsMDNode())
4828 if (!isa<DILocation>(N))
4829 return;
4830
4831 BasicBlock *BB = DII.getParent();
4832 Function *F = BB ? BB->getParent() : nullptr;
4833
4834 // The scopes for variables and !dbg attachments must agree.
4835 DILocalVariable *Var = DII.getVariable();
4836 DILocation *Loc = DII.getDebugLoc();
4837 AssertDI(Loc, "llvm.dbg." + Kind + " intrinsic requires a !dbg attachment",
4838 &DII, BB, F);
4839
4840 DISubprogram *VarSP = getSubprogram(Var->getRawScope());
4841 DISubprogram *LocSP = getSubprogram(Loc->getRawScope());
4842 if (!VarSP || !LocSP)
4843 return; // Broken scope chains are checked elsewhere.
4844
4845 AssertDI(VarSP == LocSP, "mismatched subprogram between llvm.dbg." + Kind +
4846 " variable and !dbg attachment",
4847 &DII, BB, F, Var, Var->getScope()->getSubprogram(), Loc,
4848 Loc->getScope()->getSubprogram());
4849
4850 // This check is redundant with one in visitLocalVariable().
4851 AssertDI(isType(Var->getRawType()), "invalid type ref", Var,
4852 Var->getRawType());
4853 if (auto *Type = dyn_cast_or_null<DIType>(Var->getRawType()))
4854 if (Type->isBlockByrefStruct())
4855 AssertDI(DII.getExpression() && DII.getExpression()->getNumElements(),
4856 "BlockByRef variable without complex expression", Var, &DII);
4857
4858 verifyFnArgs(DII);
4859}
4860
4861void Verifier::visitDbgLabelIntrinsic(StringRef Kind, DbgLabelInst &DLI) {
4862 AssertDI(isa<DILabel>(DLI.getRawLabel()),
4863 "invalid llvm.dbg." + Kind + " intrinsic variable", &DLI,
4864 DLI.getRawLabel());
4865
4866 // Ignore broken !dbg attachments; they're checked elsewhere.
4867 if (MDNode *N = DLI.getDebugLoc().getAsMDNode())
4868 if (!isa<DILocation>(N))
4869 return;
4870
4871 BasicBlock *BB = DLI.getParent();
4872 Function *F = BB ? BB->getParent() : nullptr;
4873
4874 // The scopes for variables and !dbg attachments must agree.
4875 DILabel *Label = DLI.getLabel();
4876 DILocation *Loc = DLI.getDebugLoc();
4877 Assert(Loc, "llvm.dbg." + Kind + " intrinsic requires a !dbg attachment",
4878 &DLI, BB, F);
4879
4880 DISubprogram *LabelSP = getSubprogram(Label->getRawScope());
4881 DISubprogram *LocSP = getSubprogram(Loc->getRawScope());
4882 if (!LabelSP || !LocSP)
4883 return;
4884
4885 AssertDI(LabelSP == LocSP, "mismatched subprogram between llvm.dbg." + Kind +
4886 " label and !dbg attachment",
4887 &DLI, BB, F, Label, Label->getScope()->getSubprogram(), Loc,
4888 Loc->getScope()->getSubprogram());
4889}
4890
4891void Verifier::verifyFragmentExpression(const DbgVariableIntrinsic &I) {
4892 DILocalVariable *V = dyn_cast_or_null<DILocalVariable>(I.getRawVariable());
4893 DIExpression *E = dyn_cast_or_null<DIExpression>(I.getRawExpression());
4894
4895 // We don't know whether this intrinsic verified correctly.
4896 if (!V || !E || !E->isValid())
4897 return;
4898
4899 // Nothing to do if this isn't a DW_OP_LLVM_fragment expression.
4900 auto Fragment = E->getFragmentInfo();
4901 if (!Fragment)
4902 return;
4903
4904 // The frontend helps out GDB by emitting the members of local anonymous
4905 // unions as artificial local variables with shared storage. When SROA splits
4906 // the storage for artificial local variables that are smaller than the entire
4907 // union, the overhang piece will be outside of the allotted space for the
4908 // variable and this check fails.
4909 // FIXME: Remove this check as soon as clang stops doing this; it hides bugs.
4910 if (V->isArtificial())
4911 return;
4912
4913 verifyFragmentExpression(*V, *Fragment, &I);
4914}
4915
4916template <typename ValueOrMetadata>
4917void Verifier::verifyFragmentExpression(const DIVariable &V,
4918 DIExpression::FragmentInfo Fragment,
4919 ValueOrMetadata *Desc) {
4920 // If there's no size, the type is broken, but that should be checked
4921 // elsewhere.
4922 auto VarSize = V.getSizeInBits();
4923 if (!VarSize)
4924 return;
4925
4926 unsigned FragSize = Fragment.SizeInBits;
4927 unsigned FragOffset = Fragment.OffsetInBits;
4928 AssertDI(FragSize + FragOffset <= *VarSize,
4929 "fragment is larger than or outside of variable", Desc, &V);
4930 AssertDI(FragSize != *VarSize, "fragment covers entire variable", Desc, &V);
4931}
4932
4933void Verifier::verifyFnArgs(const DbgVariableIntrinsic &I) {
4934 // This function does not take the scope of noninlined function arguments into
4935 // account. Don't run it if current function is nodebug, because it may
4936 // contain inlined debug intrinsics.
4937 if (!HasDebugInfo)
4938 return;
4939
4940 // For performance reasons only check non-inlined ones.
4941 if (I.getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt())
4942 return;
4943
4944 DILocalVariable *Var = I.getVariable();
4945 AssertDI(Var, "dbg intrinsic without variable");
4946
4947 unsigned ArgNo = Var->getArg();
4948 if (!ArgNo)
4949 return;
4950
4951 // Verify there are no duplicate function argument debug info entries.
4952 // These will cause hard-to-debug assertions in the DWARF backend.
4953 if (DebugFnArgs.size() < ArgNo)
4954 DebugFnArgs.resize(ArgNo, nullptr);
4955
4956 auto *Prev = DebugFnArgs[ArgNo - 1];
4957 DebugFnArgs[ArgNo - 1] = Var;
4958 AssertDI(!Prev || (Prev == Var), "conflicting debug info for argument", &I,
4959 Prev, Var);
4960}

4962void Verifier::verifyCompileUnits() {
4963 // When more than one Module is imported into the same context, such as during
4964 // an LTO build before linking the modules, ODR type uniquing may cause types
4965 // to point to a different CU. This check does not make sense in this case.
4966 if (M.getContext().isODRUniquingDebugTypes())
4967 return;
4968 auto *CUs = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.dbg.cu");
4969 SmallPtrSet<const Metadata *, 2> Listed;
4970 if (CUs)
4971 Listed.insert(CUs->op_begin(), CUs->op_end());
4972 for (auto *CU : CUVisited)
4973 AssertDI(Listed.count(CU), "DICompileUnit not listed in llvm.dbg.cu", CU);
4974 CUVisited.clear();
4975}

5001
5002bool llvm::verifyFunction(const Function &f, raw_ostream *OS) {
5003 Function &F = const_cast<Function &>(f);
5004
5005 // Don't use a raw_null_ostream. Printing IR is expensive.
5006 Verifier V(OS, /*ShouldTreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError=*/true, *f.getParent());
5007
5008 // Note that this function's return value is inverted from what you would
5009 // expect of a function called "verify".
5010 return !V.verify(F);
5011}
5012
5013bool llvm::verifyModule(const Module &M, raw_ostream *OS,
5014 bool *BrokenDebugInfo) {
5015 // Don't use a raw_null_ostream. Printing IR is expensive.
5016 Verifier V(OS, /*ShouldTreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError=*/!BrokenDebugInfo, M);
5017
5018 bool Broken = false;
5019 for (const Function &F : M)
5020 Broken |= !V.verify(F);
5021
5022 Broken |= !V.verify();
5023 if (BrokenDebugInfo)
5024 *BrokenDebugInfo = V.hasBrokenDebugInfo();
5025 // Note that this function's return value is inverted from what you would
5026 // expect of a function called "verify".
5027 return Broken;
5028}

5032struct VerifierLegacyPass : public FunctionPass {
5033 static char ID;
5034
5035 std::unique_ptr<Verifier> V;
5036 bool FatalErrors = true;
5037
5038 VerifierLegacyPass() : FunctionPass(ID) {
5039 initializeVerifierLegacyPassPass(*PassRegistry::getPassRegistry());
5040 }
5041 explicit VerifierLegacyPass(bool FatalErrors)
5042 : FunctionPass(ID),
5043 FatalErrors(FatalErrors) {
5044 initializeVerifierLegacyPassPass(*PassRegistry::getPassRegistry());
5045 }
5046
5047 bool doInitialization(Module &M) override {
5048 V = llvm::make_unique<Verifier>(
5049 &dbgs(), /*ShouldTreatBrokenDebugInfoAsError=*/false, M);
5050 return false;
5051 }
5052
5053 bool runOnFunction(Function &F) override {
5054 if (!V->verify(F) && FatalErrors) {
5055 errs() << "in function " << F.getName() << '\n';
5056 report_fatal_error("Broken function found, compilation aborted!");
5057 }
5058 return false;
5059 }
5060
5061 bool doFinalization(Module &M) override {
5062 bool HasErrors = false;
5063 for (Function &F : M)
5064 if (F.isDeclaration())
5065 HasErrors |= !V->verify(F);
5066
5067 HasErrors |= !V->verify();
5068 if (FatalErrors && (HasErrors || V->hasBrokenDebugInfo()))
5069 report_fatal_error("Broken module found, compilation aborted!");
5070 return false;
5071 }
5072
5073 void getAnalysisUsage(AnalysisUsage &AU) const override {
5074 AU.setPreservesAll();
5075 }
5076};
