5080/// Helper to issue failure from the TBAA verification
5081template <typename... Tys> void TBAAVerifier::CheckFailed(Tys &&... Args) {
5082 if (Diagnostic)
5083 return Diagnostic->CheckFailed(Args...);
5084}
5085
5086#define AssertTBAA(C, ...) \
5087 do { \
5088 if (!(C)) { \
5089 CheckFailed(__VA_ARGS__); \
5090 return false; \
5091 } \
5092 } while (false)
5093
5094/// Verify that \p BaseNode can be used as the "base type" in the struct-path
5095/// TBAA scheme. This means \p BaseNode is either a scalar node, or a
5096/// struct-type node describing an aggregate data structure (like a struct).
5097TBAAVerifier::TBAABaseNodeSummary
5098TBAAVerifier::verifyTBAABaseNode(Instruction &I, const MDNode *BaseNode,
5099 bool IsNewFormat) {
5100 if (BaseNode->getNumOperands() < 2) {
5101 CheckFailed("Base nodes must have at least two operands", &I, BaseNode);
5102 return {true, ~0u};
5103 }
5104
5105 auto Itr = TBAABaseNodes.find(BaseNode);
5106 if (Itr != TBAABaseNodes.end())
5107 return Itr->second;
5108
5109 auto Result = verifyTBAABaseNodeImpl(I, BaseNode, IsNewFormat);
5110 auto InsertResult = TBAABaseNodes.insert({BaseNode, Result});
5111 (void)InsertResult;
5112 assert(InsertResult.second && "We just checked!");
5113 return Result;
5114}
5115
5116TBAAVerifier::TBAABaseNodeSummary
5117TBAAVerifier::verifyTBAABaseNodeImpl(Instruction &I, const MDNode *BaseNode,
5118 bool IsNewFormat) {
5119 const TBAAVerifier::TBAABaseNodeSummary InvalidNode = {true, ~0u};
5120
5121 if (BaseNode->getNumOperands() == 2) {
5122 // Scalar nodes can only be accessed at offset 0.
5123 return isValidScalarTBAANode(BaseNode)
5124 ? TBAAVerifier::TBAABaseNodeSummary({false, 0})
5125 : InvalidNode;
5126 }
5127
5128 if (IsNewFormat) {
5129 if (BaseNode->getNumOperands() % 3 != 0) {
5130 CheckFailed("Access tag nodes must have the number of operands that is a "
5131 "multiple of 3!", BaseNode);
5132 return InvalidNode;
5133 }
5134 } else {
5135 if (BaseNode->getNumOperands() % 2 != 1) {
5136 CheckFailed("Struct tag nodes must have an odd number of operands!",
5137 BaseNode);
5138 return InvalidNode;
5139 }
5140 }
5141
5142 // Check the type size field.
5143 if (IsNewFormat) {
5144 auto *TypeSizeNode = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(
5145 BaseNode->getOperand(1));
5146 if (!TypeSizeNode) {
5147 CheckFailed("Type size nodes must be constants!", &I, BaseNode);
5148 return InvalidNode;
5149 }
5150 }
5151
5152 // Check the type name field. In the new format it can be anything.
5153 if (!IsNewFormat && !isa<MDString>(BaseNode->getOperand(0))) {
5154 CheckFailed("Struct tag nodes have a string as their first operand",
5155 BaseNode);
5156 return InvalidNode;
5157 }
5158
5159 bool Failed = false;
5160
5161 Optional<APInt> PrevOffset;
5162 unsigned BitWidth = ~0u;
5163
5164 // We've already checked that BaseNode is not a degenerate root node with one
5165 // operand in \c verifyTBAABaseNode, so this loop should run at least once.
5166 unsigned FirstFieldOpNo = IsNewFormat ? 3 : 1;
5167 unsigned NumOpsPerField = IsNewFormat ? 3 : 2;
5168 for (unsigned Idx = FirstFieldOpNo; Idx < BaseNode->getNumOperands();
5169 Idx += NumOpsPerField) {
5170 const MDOperand &FieldTy = BaseNode->getOperand(Idx);
5171 const MDOperand &FieldOffset = BaseNode->getOperand(Idx + 1);
5172 if (!isa<MDNode>(FieldTy)) {
5173 CheckFailed("Incorrect field entry in struct type node!", &I, BaseNode);
5174 Failed = true;
5175 continue;
5176 }
5177
5178 auto *OffsetEntryCI =
5179 mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(FieldOffset);
5180 if (!OffsetEntryCI) {
5181 CheckFailed("Offset entries must be constants!", &I, BaseNode);
5182 Failed = true;
5183 continue;
5184 }
5185
5186 if (BitWidth == ~0u)
5187 BitWidth = OffsetEntryCI->getBitWidth();
5188
5189 if (OffsetEntryCI->getBitWidth() != BitWidth) {
5190 CheckFailed(
5191 "Bitwidth between the offsets and struct type entries must match", &I,
5192 BaseNode);
5193 Failed = true;
5194 continue;
5195 }
5196
5197 // NB! As far as I can tell, we generate a non-strictly increasing offset
5198 // sequence only from structs that have zero size bit fields. When
5199 // recursing into a contained struct in \c getFieldNodeFromTBAABaseNode we
5200 // pick the field lexically the latest in struct type metadata node. This
5201 // mirrors the actual behavior of the alias analysis implementation.
5202 bool IsAscending =
5203 !PrevOffset || PrevOffset->ule(OffsetEntryCI->getValue());
5204
5205 if (!IsAscending) {
5206 CheckFailed("Offsets must be increasing!", &I, BaseNode);
5207 Failed = true;
5208 }
5209
5210 PrevOffset = OffsetEntryCI->getValue();
5211
5212 if (IsNewFormat) {
5213 auto *MemberSizeNode = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(
5214 BaseNode->getOperand(Idx + 2));
5215 if (!MemberSizeNode) {
5216 CheckFailed("Member size entries must be constants!", &I, BaseNode);
5217 Failed = true;
5218 continue;
5219 }
5220 }
5221 }
5222
5223 return Failed ? InvalidNode
5224 : TBAAVerifier::TBAABaseNodeSummary(false, BitWidth);
5225}
5226
5227static bool IsRootTBAANode(const MDNode *MD) {
5228 return MD->getNumOperands() < 2;
5229}
5230
5231static bool IsScalarTBAANodeImpl(const MDNode *MD,
5232 SmallPtrSetImpl<const MDNode *> &Visited) {
5233 if (MD->getNumOperands() != 2 && MD->getNumOperands() != 3)
5234 return false;
5235
5236 if (!isa<MDString>(MD->getOperand(0)))
5237 return false;
5238
5239 if (MD->getNumOperands() == 3) {
5240 auto *Offset = mdconst::dyn_extract<ConstantInt>(MD->getOperand(2));
5241 if (!(Offset && Offset->isZero() && isa<MDString>(MD->getOperand(0))))
5242 return false;
5243 }
5244
5245 auto *Parent = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(MD->getOperand(1));
5246 return Parent && Visited.insert(Parent).second &&
5247 (IsRootTBAANode(Parent) || IsScalarTBAANodeImpl(Parent, Visited));
5248}
5249
5250bool TBAAVerifier::isValidScalarTBAANode(const MDNode *MD) {
5251 auto ResultIt = TBAAScalarNodes.find(MD);
5252 if (ResultIt != TBAAScalarNodes.end())
5253 return ResultIt->second;
5254
5255 SmallPtrSet<const MDNode *, 4> Visited;
5256 bool Result = IsScalarTBAANodeImpl(MD, Visited);
5257 auto InsertResult = TBAAScalarNodes.insert({MD, Result});
5258 (void)InsertResult;
5259 assert(InsertResult.second && "Just checked!");
5260
5261 return Result;
5262}
5263
5264/// Returns the field node at the offset \p Offset in \p BaseNode. Update \p
5265/// Offset in place to be the offset within the field node returned.
5266///
5267/// We assume we've okayed \p BaseNode via \c verifyTBAABaseNode.
5268MDNode *TBAAVerifier::getFieldNodeFromTBAABaseNode(Instruction &I,
5269 const MDNode *BaseNode,
5270 APInt &Offset,
5271 bool IsNewFormat) {
5272 assert(BaseNode->getNumOperands() >= 2 && "Invalid base node!");
5273
5274 // Scalar nodes have only one possible "field" -- their parent in the access
5275 // hierarchy. Offset must be zero at this point, but our caller is supposed
5276 // to Assert that.
5277 if (BaseNode->getNumOperands() == 2)
5278 return cast<MDNode>(BaseNode->getOperand(1));
5279
5280 unsigned FirstFieldOpNo = IsNewFormat ? 3 : 1;
5281 unsigned NumOpsPerField = IsNewFormat ? 3 : 2;
5282 for (unsigned Idx = FirstFieldOpNo; Idx < BaseNode->getNumOperands();
5283 Idx += NumOpsPerField) {
5284 auto *OffsetEntryCI =
5285 mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(BaseNode->getOperand(Idx + 1));
5286 if (OffsetEntryCI->getValue().ugt(Offset)) {
5287 if (Idx == FirstFieldOpNo) {
5288 CheckFailed("Could not find TBAA parent in struct type node", &I,
5289 BaseNode, &Offset);
5290 return nullptr;
5291 }
5292
5293 unsigned PrevIdx = Idx - NumOpsPerField;
5294 auto *PrevOffsetEntryCI =
5295 mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(BaseNode->getOperand(PrevIdx + 1));
5296 Offset -= PrevOffsetEntryCI->getValue();
5297 return cast<MDNode>(BaseNode->getOperand(PrevIdx));
5298 }
5299 }
5300
5301 unsigned LastIdx = BaseNode->getNumOperands() - NumOpsPerField;
5302 auto *LastOffsetEntryCI = mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(
5303 BaseNode->getOperand(LastIdx + 1));
5304 Offset -= LastOffsetEntryCI->getValue();
5305 return cast<MDNode>(BaseNode->getOperand(LastIdx));
5306}
5307
5308static bool isNewFormatTBAATypeNode(llvm::MDNode *Type) {
5309 if (!Type || Type->getNumOperands() < 3)
5310 return false;
5311
5312 // In the new format type nodes shall have a reference to the parent type as
5313 // its first operand.
5314 MDNode *Parent = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(Type->getOperand(0));
5315 if (!Parent)
5316 return false;
5317
5318 return true;
5319}
5320
5321bool TBAAVerifier::visitTBAAMetadata(Instruction &I, const MDNode *MD) {
5322 AssertTBAA(isa<LoadInst>(I) || isa<StoreInst>(I) || isa<CallInst>(I) ||
5323 isa<VAArgInst>(I) || isa<AtomicRMWInst>(I) ||
5324 isa<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I),
5325 "This instruction shall not have a TBAA access tag!", &I);
5326
5327 bool IsStructPathTBAA =
5328 isa<MDNode>(MD->getOperand(0)) && MD->getNumOperands() >= 3;
5329
5330 AssertTBAA(
5331 IsStructPathTBAA,
5332 "Old-style TBAA is no longer allowed, use struct-path TBAA instead", &I);
5333
5334 MDNode *BaseNode = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(MD->getOperand(0));
5335 MDNode *AccessType = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(MD->getOperand(1));
5336
5337 bool IsNewFormat = isNewFormatTBAATypeNode(AccessType);
5338
5339 if (IsNewFormat) {
5340 AssertTBAA(MD->getNumOperands() == 4 || MD->getNumOperands() == 5,
5341 "Access tag metadata must have either 4 or 5 operands", &I, MD);
5342 } else {
5343 AssertTBAA(MD->getNumOperands() < 5,
5344 "Struct tag metadata must have either 3 or 4 operands", &I, MD);
5345 }
5346
5347 // Check the access size field.
5348 if (IsNewFormat) {
5349 auto *AccessSizeNode = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(
5350 MD->getOperand(3));
5351 AssertTBAA(AccessSizeNode, "Access size field must be a constant", &I, MD);
5352 }
5353
5354 // Check the immutability flag.
5355 unsigned ImmutabilityFlagOpNo = IsNewFormat ? 4 : 3;
5356 if (MD->getNumOperands() == ImmutabilityFlagOpNo + 1) {
5357 auto *IsImmutableCI = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(
5358 MD->getOperand(ImmutabilityFlagOpNo));
5359 AssertTBAA(IsImmutableCI,
5360 "Immutability tag on struct tag metadata must be a constant",
5361 &I, MD);
5362 AssertTBAA(
5363 IsImmutableCI->isZero() || IsImmutableCI->isOne(),
5364 "Immutability part of the struct tag metadata must be either 0 or 1",
5365 &I, MD);
5366 }
5367
5368 AssertTBAA(BaseNode && AccessType,
5369 "Malformed struct tag metadata: base and access-type "
5370 "should be non-null and point to Metadata nodes",
5371 &I, MD, BaseNode, AccessType);
5372
5373 if (!IsNewFormat) {
5374 AssertTBAA(isValidScalarTBAANode(AccessType),
5375 "Access type node must be a valid scalar type", &I, MD,
5376 AccessType);
5377 }
5378
5379 auto *OffsetCI = mdconst::dyn_extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(MD->getOperand(2));
5380 AssertTBAA(OffsetCI, "Offset must be constant integer", &I, MD);
5381
5382 APInt Offset = OffsetCI->getValue();
5383 bool SeenAccessTypeInPath = false;
5384
5385 SmallPtrSet<MDNode *, 4> StructPath;
5386
5387 for (/* empty */; BaseNode && !IsRootTBAANode(BaseNode);
5388 BaseNode = getFieldNodeFromTBAABaseNode(I, BaseNode, Offset,
5389 IsNewFormat)) {
5390 if (!StructPath.insert(BaseNode).second) {
5391 CheckFailed("Cycle detected in struct path", &I, MD);
5392 return false;
5393 }
5394
5395 bool Invalid;
5396 unsigned BaseNodeBitWidth;
5397 std::tie(Invalid, BaseNodeBitWidth) = verifyTBAABaseNode(I, BaseNode,
5398 IsNewFormat);
5399
5400 // If the base node is invalid in itself, then we've already printed all the
5401 // errors we wanted to print.
5402 if (Invalid)
5403 return false;
5404
5405 SeenAccessTypeInPath |= BaseNode == AccessType;
5406
5407 if (isValidScalarTBAANode(BaseNode) || BaseNode == AccessType)
5408 AssertTBAA(Offset == 0, "Offset not zero at the point of scalar access",
5409 &I, MD, &Offset);
5410
5411 AssertTBAA(BaseNodeBitWidth == Offset.getBitWidth() ||
5412 (BaseNodeBitWidth == 0 && Offset == 0) ||
5413 (IsNewFormat && BaseNodeBitWidth == ~0u),
5414 "Access bit-width not the same as description bit-width", &I, MD,
5415 BaseNodeBitWidth, Offset.getBitWidth());
5416
5417 if (IsNewFormat && SeenAccessTypeInPath)
5418 break;
5419 }
5420
5421 AssertTBAA(SeenAccessTypeInPath, "Did not see access type in access path!",
5422 &I, MD);
5423 return true;
5424}
